DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Join us for our weekly Wednesday night contra
  dance! Bring an instrument to join the open band this week\, or sign up to
  call a dance. <br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance I
 nformation</b></span></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.<br></spa
 n></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Beginner lesson at 7:10 p.m. 
 (try to arrive by 7 to register as a member)<br></span></span></li> &nbsp\;
  &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><li><span><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and mas
 ks required (see more details below)</span></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li>
 <span><span>Entrance fee by donation after becoming a member (suggested ran
 ge is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></li><
 /ul><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Details</b></span><br><b>Up
 -to-date vaccination is required</b>. This means that if your 2nd dose of a
  Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</span> was at least 5 months ago or your s
 ingle dose of a Johnson &amp\; Johnson <span>vaccine</span> was at least 2 
 months ago\, you will need to show us evidence of a booster shot. (For our 
 purposes\, even if you are eligible for more than one booster shot\, only o
 ne is required.) If we have not yet seen proof of your most recent vaccinat
 ion\, please send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncont
 ra.org"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by th
 e end of Tuesday\, or bring the card or a photo of it with you to the dance
 .<b><i> </i></b>Thank you for helping to keep us all safe!</span><br><br><s
 pan><b>Membership is required.</b> Becoming a member is easy!&nbsp\;</span>
 </span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span>1) Fill <span>in a membership
  form at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/uplo
 ads/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf"><b><u>print one</u></b></a> to compl
 ete in advance.&nbsp\;</span></span></span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span
 ><span><span>2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a href="mai
 lto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloom
 ingtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance.&nbsp\;</span><
 /span></span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span><span>3) Pay $12 either
  at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/"><b
 ><u>online</u></b></a> ($2 for those under 30). </span><br><br><b>Masks are
  required. </b>Masks must cover the mouth and nose at all times in the danc
 e hall and when entering the building. Dancers can step outside the dance h
 all to drink water. <br><br><b>This dance is run by donation</b>\, with a s
 uggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least som
 ething because the event is sustained by the community. We estimate that if
  everyone were to give $10\, we would break even after paying the rental fe
 e and the performers. Donations may be made <a href="http://bloomingtoncont
 ra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/"><b><u>online</
 u></b></a> or at the door.</span></span>&nbsp\;<u></u><u></u><u></u></html-
 blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221123T142917Z
