DESCRIPTION:<html-blob>Join us for our weekly Wednesday night contra dance!
 <br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Information</b><
 /span></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.<br></span></span></li> 
 &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Beginner lesson at 8 p.m. sharp<br></span></
 span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><li><span><span>Vaccines\, me
 mbership\, and masks required (see more details below)</span></span></li> &
 nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Entrance fee by donation after becoming a mem
 ber (suggested range is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</
 span></span></li></ul><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Details</
 b></span><br><b>Up-to-date vaccination is required</b>. This means that if 
 your 2nd dose of a Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</span> was at least 5 mo
 nths ago or your single dose of a Johnson &amp\; Johnson <span>vaccine</spa
 n> was at least 2 months ago\, you will need to show us evidence of a boost
 er shot. (For our purposes\, even if you are eligible for more than one boo
 ster shot\, only one is required.) If we have not yet seen proof of your mo
 st recent vaccination\, please send a photo to <a href="mailto:communicatio
 ns@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org
 </u></b></a> by the end of Tuesday\, or bring the card or a photo of it wit
 h you to the dance.<b><i> </i></b>Thank you for helping to keep us all safe
 !</span><br><br><span><b>Membership is required.</b> Becoming a member is e
 asy! 1) Fill <span>in a membership form at the dance or <a href="http://blo
 omingtoncontra.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf"><b
 ><u>print one</u></b></a> to complete in advance. 2) Send proof of up-to-da
 te vaccination to </span><a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.o
 rg"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or 
 bring it to the dance. 3) Pay $12 either at the dance or <a href="http://bl
 oomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/"><b><u>online</u></b></a> ($2 for thos
 e under 30). </span><br><br><b>Masks are required. </b>Masks must cover the
  mouth and nose at all times in the dance hall and when entering the buildi
 ng. Dancers can step outside the dance hall to drink water. At Windfall\, t
 here is also a designated room where masks are optional.<br><br><b>This dan
 ce is run by donation</b>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope 
 that everyone will give at least something because the event is sustained b
 y the community. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would b
 reak even after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be 
 made <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-th
 e-covid-19-downtime/"><b><u>online</u></b></a> or at the door.</span></span
 >&nbsp\;</html-blob>
