 ewenthal\, Jamie Gans\, Rob Fischman\, and Michael Valliant)\, with calling
  by Susan English of Wooster\, Ohio. This is our very first chance\, since 
 we were all scattered\, to get to dance to the music of the storied Bloomin
 gton contra band Ox on Fire! Come out to welcome them back and enjoy the ol
 d timey musicianship of this deeply rooted group\, with Tamara\, Jamie\, Ro
 b\, and Michael on more instruments than we can count here (most likely at 
 the very least a bass\, a guitar\, a fiddle or two\, and a banjo . . .) and
  all pulled together\, through the magic of long-distance technology\, with
  the warm\, thoughtful\, experienced calling of Susan English.<br><br><font
 ><span>Join us using your computer or mobile device&nbsp\;for fellowship\, 
 music\, and even some virtual dancing while we deal with the restrictions d
 ue to the COVID-19 pandemic.&nbsp\; See our Email newsletter for details or
  contact <span><a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">commun
 ications@bloomingtoncontra.org</a></span><span></span></span></font><br><fo
 nt><span><span></span></span></font>
