DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><span><span><span><b>Weekly Dance Information</b></s
 pan></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.</span></span></li><li><sp
 an><span>Harmony School (909 E 2nd St\, Bloomington)</span></span></li><li>
 <span><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and masks required (see more details be
 low)</span></span></li><li><span><span>Entrance fee by donation (suggested 
 range is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></l
 i></ul><span><span><span><b><span>Beginner Dance Lesson Every Week</span></
 b></span><span> - New</span> and <span>beginner</span> dancers are welcome 
 to become members and dance with us! New dancers should try to arrive at 7 
 p.m. to check in at the welcome table. A beginner lesson will be offered by
  the caller every week at 7:10 p.m. before the dance. </span></span></html-
 blob><br><html-blob><br><span><span><strong>Up-to-date vaccination is requi
 red</strong>. </span></span><span><span>This means that if your 2nd dose of
  a Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</span> was at least 5 months ago or your
  single dose of a Johnson &amp\; Johnson <span>vaccine</span> was at least 
 2 months ago\, you will need to show us evidence of a booster shot.</span><
 /span><span><span> If we have not yet seen proof of your most recent vaccin
 ation\, please send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtonco
 ntra.org"><b><u>communications@bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by the end
  of Tuesday\, or bring the card or a photo of it with you to the dance.</sp
 an></span><span><span><strong><em> </em></strong>Thank you for helping to k
 eep us all safe!</span></span><span><span><br><br><strong>Membership is req
 uired.</strong> Becoming a members is easy! 1) fill <span>in a membership f
 orm at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/upload
 s/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf">print one</a> to complete in advance. 
 2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a href="mailto:communica
 tions@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@bloomingtoncontra.org </u
 ></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance. 3) Pay $12 either at the dance or 
 <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/">online</a> ($2 for 
 those under 30). </span><br><br><strong>Masks are required. </strong>Masks 
 must cover the mouth and nose at all times. Dancers can step outside for a 
 mask break or may step into the hallway to take a drink of water.<br><br><s
 trong>This dance is run by donation</strong>\, with a suggested range from 
 $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least something because the e
 vent is sustained by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to gi
 ve $10\, we would break even after paying the rental fee and the performers
 . Donations may be made <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-p
 erformers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">online</a> or at the door.</span><
 /span><br><br><span>&nbsp\;</span>&nbsp\;<span><span></span></span></html-b
 lob>
