UID:14bs14befau5o7b93e9dg14skn@google.com
CREATED:20210508T142303Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span><strong>BOTMDG Baby Steps - In-Person Dance at Open
  Mic Night June 2nd</strong><br><br><strong>Wednesday\, June 2\, 2021</stro
 ng>\, our Bloomington contra <strong>callers and musicians open mic night</
 strong> will be an in-person dance (with a lot of caveats and conditions\, 
 see below) at the Big Shelter at Marci Jane Lewis Park\, 106 South Park Str
 eet\, in Ellettsville. Parking adjacent to shelter. Stage is plywood&nbsp\;
 but shelter main floor&nbsp\;is concrete\, sorry.<br>&nbsp\;<br><strong>MUS
 T BE VACCINATED •&nbsp\;MEMBERS ONLY • NO CONTRA LINE • NO ENTRANCE FEE • N
 O BATHROOMS • NO ZOOM</strong><br>&nbsp\;<br>The dance will start at 8\, bu
 t you are very welcome to come by around 7:30 or before to help us set up (
 several sets of very large\, heavy bleachers need to be moved out of the wa
 y ahead of time and moved back into place at the end of the night).<br>&nbs
 p\;<br>You MUST be vaccinated and a member of BOTMDG (Bloomington contra) t
 o take part in this dance (also applies to our open mic night performers). 
 Please e-mail a picture of your vaccination card to us (by midnight Tuesday
 ) at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@<
 wbr>bloomingtoncontra.org</a> or else bring it with you on Wednesday night.
  Unfortunately\, we cannot let you join the dance or the open mic night per
 formers if you cannot show us you are vaccinated.*<br><em>*Children too you
 ng to be eligible for vaccination may come with their parents and MUST stay
  in their parents’ space on the dance floor. Maximum number of people per p
 od remains 4.</em><br>&nbsp\;<br>This first experiment will NOT involve a c
 ontra line where everyone dances with everyone else. (We hope to be able to
  try that later in the month\, but we are starting as cautiously as we can.
 ) Please come prepared to dance in a delineated space either by yourself or
  with up to 3 others that you have planned to dance with ahead of time. Max
 imum 4 per pod.&nbsp\;<strong>There will not be crossing of lines or mixing
  of groups on this first experimental in-person night\; please help us make
  this a successful night where all can feel safe.</strong> If you haven’t t
 aken part in any of our Zoom contra nights and/or have never tried doing a 
 contra night with just 1\, 2\, 3\, or 4 dancers\, please come and try anywa
 y - our callers will help you\, and you can watch what the others are doing
  in their spaces as well. (And if you come early we can demonstrate.)<br>&n
 bsp\;<br>If you don’t want to dance at all\, you may of course stay on the 
 sidelines. If you want to be inside the shelter or in the immediate vicinit
 y\, we will still need to see your proof of vaccination. You are very welco
 me to be masked but there is no requirement to be so.<br>&nbsp\;<br>There i
 s no entrance fee for this dance! Donations for the performers will be very
  gladly accepted at the dance or at our online Paypal site.<br>&nbsp\;<br>W
 e have been told that there is no bathroom available at the park for the mo
 nth of June. Alcohol is not permitted. We will not be serving food or drink
 s but you can bring your own.<br>&nbsp\;<br>We won’t be Zooming this dance.
  We will be sorry to miss our farflung and faithful Zoom friends\; but for 
 this dance we are going to focus on trying to make the live dance work.<br>
 &nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;<br><strong>MUST BE VACCINATED •&nbsp\;MEMBERS ONLY • NO 
 CONTRA LINE • NO ENTRANCE FEE • NO BATHROOMS • NO ZOOM</strong></span></spa
 n><br><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></spa
 n></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210601T145744Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:In-Person Open Mic Night (Open Band and Open Calling)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
