DESCRIPTION:<span><span><strong><span>July</span> 21</strong>: Maxwell Rove
 rs - Scott Anderson (guitar)\, Amber Challifour (accordion)\, Larry Moss (f
 iddle)\, Mark Wiedenmayer (bass)\, with Kyla Wargel calling&nbsp\;</span></
 span><br><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span><br><span><span><span><span><span
 ><strong>Wednesday Night Dance Details</strong></span><br><span><strong>Vac
 cines are required</strong>.&nbsp\;We will need to see your vaccination car
 d\, if you haven't already shared it with us. Either send a photo to <a hre
 f="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@<wbr>bloomin
 gtoncontra.org</a> by the end of Tuesday\, or bring it with you to the danc
 e. </span><br><br>This is a <strong>members-only</strong> dance. Becoming a
  member is easy - <span>you can do so online at&nbsp\;<a href="https://bloo
 mingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&
 amp\;id=ffafc37ce6&amp\;e=aa19521646">http://bloomingtoncontra.<wbr>org/bec
 ome-a-member/</a>\, or you can bring $12 to the dance. Note: membership for
  anyone under 30 years old is only $2!</span><br><br><span>Dances begin at 
 <strong>7:30 p.m. Eastern</strong>. </span>The last waltz will conclude by 
 8:45 p.m. to allow time for cleanup. You are welcome to come early to help 
 set up or stay late to help pack up.<br><br>Events will be in-person at the
  Big Shelter at <strong>Marci Jane Lewis Park</strong>\, 106 South Park Str
 eet\, in Ellettsville - just 15 minutes from downtown Bloomington!<strong> 
 </strong></span></span><br><br><span><span><span>This dance is run <strong>
 by donation</strong>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that 
 everyone will give at least something\, even if it's very little\, because 
 the event is sustained by the community. We will continue to give 100% of t
 he donations to the performers.</span> <span>Donations may be made in perso
 n or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=
 0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=067fffa0b5&amp\;e=aa19521646">here</a>.</
 span><br><br><span><strong><span>Contra</span> Line! or pods! or listening 
 and watching!</strong> There is plenty of space to participate at your comf
 ort level\, and we will remind people at the dance not to assume anything a
 bout what someone else might be comfortable with and to ask about and respe
 ct others' boundaries. Special wristbands will be offered for people who wa
 nt to indicate that they don't want to do neighbor swings or want to do two
 -hand turns in place of swings. We want to be <em>even more</em> respectful
  than usual of individual boundaries and take nothing for granted about peo
 ple's consent. </span><br><br><span>In the case of <strong>rain</strong>\, 
 the dance will go on - if it's thundering\, we will have to see (but come o
 n out so we can figure it out together)!</span></span></span><br><br><span>
 <span><strong>No Zoom</strong> - Unfortunately\, the best venues we've foun
 d for in-person\, outdoor\, covered\, spacious events do not work well for 
 using internet.</span></span><br><br><span><span>Previously\, <strong>bathr
 ooms </strong>were available at the nearby baseball field. We are not sure 
 if they will be available every week.</span></span><br><br><span><span><br>
 <span><strong>TONS OF FUN AND HAPPINESS • MUST BE VACCINATED AND BECOME A M
 EMBER </strong></span></span></span>&nbsp\;</span></span>
