DTEND:20210401T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020722Z
UID:38mhin2tdn0kqhv4d22opsgfkt@google.com
CREATED:20210226T221259Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Entwyned is John Paolillo on mandolin-family instruments 
 (including mandola\, bouzouki\, and mandocello) and Twy Bethard on fiddle\,
  nyckelharpa\, and keyboard. John and Twy play folk tunes - compelling Celt
 ic-influenced melodies\, friendly old-time tunes\, haunting Scandinavian so
 ngs - accented with influences from world music\, swing\, and popular tunes
 \, all driven by a lively rhythmic flow.  Jonathan Sivier has been involved
  in traditional dance since 1987.  He has been leading dances since 1992.  
 He is active with the Urbana Country Dancers and is one of the leaders of t
 he Central Illinois English Country Dancers.  He regularly calls contra\, E
 nglish and square dances in Champaign-Urbana and elsewhere.  He has led dan
 ces at various locations in Florida\, Hawaii\, Illinois\, Indiana\, Iowa\, 
 Kentucky\, Michigan\, Missouri\, Ohio and West Virginia.</span><br><span><s
 pan>&nbsp\;<br><span>---------- </span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If 
 you'd like the Zoom link\, please email us at <span><span>at <a href="mailt
 o:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@bloomingtoncontra.or
 g</a></span></span>.</span></span></span><br><span><span><span>As of March\
 , all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begin at <b>8 p.m. Eastern</b>.</span></span>
 </span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you haven’t been to one of our o
 nline events\, you might be wondering what to expect! As our musicians play
  for us\, and the caller calls\, you are welcome to dance with us in your o
 wn space\, play along with the musicians with your mic muted\, or just watc
 h and listen. We also try to check in with everyone briefly each week. The 
 music lasts until about 8:45\, followed by the check-in.</span></span></spa
 n><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>Waltzes are easy to dance alone or with 
 a partner. Up-tempo tunes will sometimes have <span>contra</span>-like call
 ing\, but for the times when there is no calling\, please feel free to danc
 e along at home with <span>contra</span> moves of your choice. Or just boog
 ie down to the amazing music!</span></span>&nbsp\; </span><br><br><span>---
 -------</span><span><br></span><br><span>We are grateful for all donations\
 , and happy to be able to keep paying our musicians and dance leaders durin
 g these unusual times. You can find our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.o
 rg/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">PayPal donation bu
 tton on our website</a>.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; </span></span><br></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210226T222447Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Zoom Event: Entwyned with caller Jonathan Sivier
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
