CREATED:20121228T143818Z
DESCRIPTION:Sixth Annual Percussive Dance Extravaganza: Now We Are Six show
 cases the local talent that has grown through the years and come into its o
 wn via this performance opportunity. This year's featured musician will be 
 Brad Leftwich\, a master Old Time fiddler and vocalist. Playing alongside B
 rad will be Jamie Gans on fiddle\, Sam Bartlett on banjo and mandolin\, wit
 h Jim Nelson (guitar) and Dedo Norris (bass) from St Louis\, anchoring the 
 rhythm section. The dancers\, led by Bloomington's own Tamara Loewenthal\, 
 will perform various rhythmic footwork\, spanning flatfooting and clogging\
 , tap and French Canadian\, English wooden shoe and Long sword dances. Addi
 tional performers include Grey Larsen\, Annie Bartlett\, Suzannah Edgar\, M
 ary Beth Roska\, Cliff Emery\, Allana Radecki\, Katie Zukof\, Eric Schedler
 \, Tim Moore\, Dena\, El Saffar\, and many more!\n\nDoors open at 7:00pm. T
 ickets are $15 in advance\, $18 day of show. Advance tickets may be purchas
 ed at Bloomingfoods East or West\, or by calling (812) 333-3180 or by email
 ing tamaradancer@gmail.com\n\nThis year\, for the first time\, the Extravag
 anza Band will linger to play an Old Time Square Dance! \n\nMore info avail
 able at: http://www.facebook.com/events/114161248750400/
LAST-MODIFIED:20221121T184313Z
LOCATION:Rhino’s All-Ages Club\, 331 S Walnut St.
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sixth Annual Percussive Dance Extravaganza
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
