UID:2a0ia14l7isgcqc6ei9iu0guch@google.com
CREATED:20210715T222803Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Open mic night led by Twy Bethard and John Paolillo</span
 >&nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span><strong>Wednesday Night Dance Deta
 ils</strong></span><br><span><strong>Vaccines are required</strong>.&nbsp\;
 We will need to see your vaccination card\, if you haven't already shared i
 t with us. Either send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingto
 ncontra.org">communications@<wbr>bloomingtoncontra.org</a> by the end of Tu
 esday\, or bring it with you to the dance. </span><br><br>This is a <strong
 >members-only</strong> dance. Becoming a member is easy - <span>you can do 
 so online at&nbsp\;<a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/
 track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=ffafc37ce6&amp\;e=aa1952164
 6">http://bloomingtoncontra.<wbr>org/become-a-member/</a>\, or you can brin
 g $12 to the dance. Note: membership for anyone under 30 years old is only 
 $2!</span><br><br><span>Dances begin at <strong>7:30 p.m. Eastern</strong>.
  </span>The last waltz will conclude by 8:45 p.m. to allow time for cleanup
 . You are welcome to come early to help set up or stay late to help pack up
 .<br><br>Events will be in-person at the Big Shelter at <strong>Marci Jane 
 Lewis Park</strong>\, 106 South Park Street\, in Ellettsville - just 15 min
 utes from downtown Bloomington!<strong> </strong></span></span><br><br><spa
 n><span><span>This dance is run <strong>by donation</strong>\, with a sugge
 sted range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least somethi
 ng\, even if it's very little\, because the event is sustained by the commu
 nity. We will continue to give 100% of the donations to the performers.</sp
 an> <span>Donations may be made in person or <a href="https://bloomingtonco
 ntra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=0
 67fffa0b5&amp\;e=aa19521646">here</a>.</span><br><br><span><strong><span>Co
 ntra</span> Line! or pods! or listening and watching!</strong> There is ple
 nty of space to participate at your comfort level\, and we will remind peop
 le at the dance not to assume anything about what someone else might be com
 fortable with and to ask about and respect others' boundaries. Special wris
 tbands will be offered for people who want to indicate that they don't want
  to do neighbor swings or want to do two-hand turns in place of swings. We 
 want to be <em>even more</em> respectful than usual of individual boundarie
 s and take nothing for granted about people's consent. </span><br><br><span
 >In the case of <strong>rain</strong>\, the dance will go on - if it's thun
 dering\, we will have to see (but come on out so we can figure it out toget
 her)!</span></span></span><br><br><span><span><strong>No Zoom</strong> - Un
 fortunately\, the best venues we've found for in-person\, outdoor\, covered
 \, spacious events do not work well for using internet.</span></span><br><b
 r><span><span>Previously\, <strong>bathrooms </strong>were available at the
  nearby baseball field. We are not sure if they will be available every wee
 k.</span></span><br><br><span><span><br><span><strong>TONS OF FUN AND HAPPI
 NESS • MUST BE VACCINATED AND BECOME A MEMBER&nbsp\; </strong></span></span
 ></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210715T222803Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Open mic night led by Twy Bethard and John Paolillo
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
