UID:351rbaav8ino3o4s1lqjgkdnt9@google.com
CREATED:20211028T150409Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><span><span>Please come and join us for a community <span>p
 otluck</span> at the Sycamore Shelter at Lower Cascades on Saturday\, the 3
 0th\, from 4 to 6:30 p.m. (More info about&nbsp\;the shelter below.) </span
 ></span><ul><li><span><span>Bring food to share and your own beverages - BO
 TMDG&nbsp\;will provide paper products.</span></span></li><li><span><span>L
 et us know if you would like to use the grills\, so we can be prepared with
  charcoal.</span></span></li><li><span><span>Please feel free to bring your
  friends or family - non-members welcome - kids included</span></span></li>
 <li><span><span>Besides just being together as a group and enjoying our <sp
 an>potluck</span> together\, we will</span></span><ul><li><span><span>hang 
 out around the fire (let us know if you have firewood you can bring)</span>
 </span></li><li><span><span>introduce board members and talk about board po
 sitions (elections coming up in January)</span></span></li><li><span><span>
 have song books and maybe sing (trying to stay Covid safe while doing so) -
  bring instruments!</span></span></li><li><span><span>potentially play some
  games</span></span></li></ul></li><li><span><span>If we don't already have
  your vaccination info on file\, please&nbsp\;bring proof of vaccination (p
 hoto or paper record\, unless under 12)</span></span></li></ul><br><span><s
 pan>***Information about the shelter:<br>The Sycamore Shelter is located in
  the lower portion of Cascades Park. You must access Lower Cascades either 
 from W Club House Dr off Kinser Pike or from W Old SR 37 off of N Walnut St
  (at the light on the way out of Bloomington). The other accesses to Cascad
 es are closed to vehicular traffic due to construction.&nbsp\; Two bathroom
 s are a part of the building. The shelter comes equipped with grills\, elec
 tricity\, fireplace\, water and drinking fountain\, playground access\, and
  a large parking lot. The Sycamore Shelter is wheelchair accessible.</span>
 </span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211028T150409Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:BOTMDG Potluck at Lower Cascades
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
