DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20220803T214500
DTSTAMP:20260309T020722Z
UID:570mkt0n9m6qh76u7ne9kop5o9_R20220804T001500@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20220803T201500
CREATED:20220702T175218Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for our weekly Wednesday night contra dance!<br>&nbsp\;
 <br><span><span><span><strong>Weekly Wednesday Dance Information</strong></
 span></span></span><ul><li><span><span>8:15-9:45 p.m.<br></span></span></li
 > &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Beginner lesson at 8 p.m. sharp<br></span>
 </span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><li><span><span>Vaccines\, 
 membership\, and masks required (see more details below)</span></span></li>
  &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Entrance fee by donation after becoming a m
 ember (suggested range is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)
 </span></span></li></ul><span><span><span><strong>Weekly Wednesday Dance De
 tails</strong></span><br><strong>Up-to-date vaccination is required</strong
 >. This means that if your 2nd dose of a Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</s
 pan> was at least 5 months ago or your single dose of a Johnson &amp\; John
 son <span>vaccine</span> was at least 2 months ago\, you will need to show 
 us evidence of a booster shot. (For our purposes\, even if you are eligible
  for more than one booster shot\, only one is required.) If we have not yet
  seen proof of your most recent vaccination\, please send a photo to <a hre
 f="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<wbr>b
 loomingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by the end of Tuesday\, or bring the card 
 or a photo of it with you to the dance.<strong><em> </em></strong>Thank you
  for helping to keep us all safe!</span><br><br><span><strong>Membership is
  required.</strong> Becoming a member is easy! 1) Fill <span>in a membershi
 p form at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/upl
 oads/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf"><b><u>print one</u></b></a> to comp
 lete in advance. 2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a href=
 "mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<wbr>blo
 omingtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance. 3) Pay $12 e
 ither at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member
 /"><b><u>online</u></b></a> ($2 for those under 30). </span><br><br><strong
 >Masks are required. </strong>Masks must cover the mouth and nose at all ti
 mes in the dance hall and when entering the building. Dancers can step outs
 ide the dance hall to drink water. At Windfall\, there is also a designated
  room where masks are optional.<br><br><strong>This dance is run by donatio
 n</strong>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone w
 ill give at least something because the event is sustained by the community
 . We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would break even after
  paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be made <a href="h
 ttp://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-down
 time/"><b><u>online</u></b></a> or at the door.</span></span>&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20220818T230437Z
LOCATION:Windfall Dancers Inc\, 1101 N Dunn St\, Bloomington\, IN 47408\, U
 SA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Contra Dance at Windfall - Open Mic Night (band led by Sam Bartlett
 )
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
