DESCRIPTION: <strong>About Our Dances</strong><ul><li><strong>Time: </stron
 g>7:30-9:30 p.m.</li>   <li><strong>Location</strong>: Harmony School\, 909
  E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401</li>   <li><strong>Entrance fee</stron
 g>: by sliding scale donation\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We h
 ope that everyone will give at least something because the event is sustain
 ed by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we wou
 ld break even after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may
  be made <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://bloomingtoncontra.us
 13.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D0c065082be7e5f22020734e68%26id%3D298b3f5
 5c0%26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=16962852860425
 54&amp\;usg=AOvVaw1aM--Ux-NDs99OUIDjfC1C" target="_blank"><u><u><b><u>onlin
 e</u></b></u></u></a> or at the door. </li>   <li><strong>Striving Toward S
 afe Space Policy</strong>: We hope to create a dance in which everyone feel
 s safe and welcome. Please take a moment to review our <a href="https://www
 .google.com/url?q=https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/clic
 k?u%3D0c065082be7e5f22020734e68%26id%3D5d4959b742%26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=
 D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1696285286042554&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0caKm3lZvwx
 S3j1G3pcwhT" target="_blank"><u><u><b><u>policy</u></b></u></u></a> on resp
 ect and consent.</li></ul><strong>Covid Policies</strong>   <br><ul><li><st
 rong>Membership Requirement</strong>: Becoming a member is easy! As of July
  1\, 2023\, membership is now optional for all our dances. Becoming a membe
 r is easy!</li><li>   1) Fill out a membership form at the dance.<br>   2) 
 Pay $10 either at the dance or <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https:
 //bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D0c065082be7e5f2202
 0734e68%26id%3D92fa0d4267%26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&a
 mp\;ust=1696285286042554&amp\;usg=AOvVaw1om_KceSSVZTiwoaNjKEiR" target="_bl
 ank"><u><u><b><u>online</u></b></u></u></a> (free for those 15 and under). 
 </li>   <li><strong>Vaccination Requirements</strong>: As of May 31\, 2023\
 , we are no longer requiring proof of vaccination.</li>   <li><strong>Masks
  Encouraged</strong>: Masks are required if you have been exposed to COVID 
 recently.</li>   <li><strong>Stay home if you...</strong>    <ul>       <li
 >have symptoms of COVID (which could also mean cold or flu symptoms)\, rega
 rdless of whether or not you tested for COVID</li>       <li>first tested p
 ositive for COVID within the last 5 days\, even without symptoms </li>     
   <li>first tested positive for COVID more than 5 days ago and still have a
  fever\, and/or your symptoms are not yet getting better</li>  <br></ul></l
 i><li><strong>Exercise caution and wear a mask if... </strong>    <ul>     
   <li>you have been exposed to someone who has tested positive (spent more 
 than 15 minutes less than 6 feet away from them\, without masks on\, indoor
 s\, or spent 20 minutes or more in intense conversation or close proximity 
 even outdoors\, without masks on)        <ul>           <li>err on the cons
 ervative side</li>           <li>watch yourself for symptoms</li>          
  <li>take a COVID test on day 5 </li></ul></li>       <li>If the exposure h
 appened within 5 days of the dance\, it is probably wisest to stay home the
 n\, too\, until you have a chance to test yourself. Please note that this i
 s more conservative than the CDC&#39\;s guidelines at this point.</li></ul>
 </li>   <li><strong>Notify us if...</strong><strong> </strong>   <ul>      
  <li>you are diagnosed with COVID-19 within 10 days of attending any BOTMDG
  event\, please let the board know\, at <a href="mailto:communications@bloo
 mingtoncontra.org" target="_blank"><u><u><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomi
 ngtoncontra.org</u></b></u></u></a>\, within 24 hours of your diagnosis if 
 you possibly can\, so that we can inform others.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li
 >    </li></ul>
