CREATED:20210715T223050Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Supertrad - Sam Bartlett (banjo) and Eric Schedler (accor
 dion)\, with Kyla Wargel calling</span>&nbsp\;<br><br>*This week - beginner
  lesson at 7:15! Invite your friends!* <br><br><span><span><span><b>Wednesd
 ay Night Dance Details</b></span><br><span><b>Vaccines are required</b>.&nb
 sp\;We will need to see your vaccination card\, if you haven't already shar
 ed it with us. Either send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomi
 ngtoncontra.org">communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</a> by the end
  of Tuesday\, or bring it with you to the dance. </span><br><br>This is a <
 b>members-only</b> dance. Becoming a member is easy - <span>you can do so o
 nline at&nbsp\;<a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/trac
 k/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=ffafc37ce6&e=aa19521646">http://bloo
 mingtoncontra.<u></u>org/become-a-member/</a>\, or you can bring $12 to the
  dance. Note: membership for anyone under 30 years old is only $2!</span><b
 r><br><span>Dances begin at <b>7:30 p.m. Eastern</b>. </span>The last waltz
  will conclude by 8:45 p.m. to allow time for cleanup. You are welcome to c
 ome early to help set up or stay late to help pack up.<br><br>Events will b
 e in-person at the Big Shelter at <b>Marci Jane Lewis Park</b>\, 106 South 
 Park Street\, in Ellettsville - just 15 minutes from downtown Bloomington!<
 b> </b></span></span><br><br><span><span><span>This dance is run <b>by dona
 tion</b>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone wil
 l give at least something\, even if it's very little\, because the event is
  sustained by the community. We will continue to give 100% of the donations
  to the performers.</span> <span>Donations may be made in person or <a href
 ="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e
 5f22020734e68&id=067fffa0b5&e=aa19521646">here</a>.</span><br><br><span><b>
 <span>Contra</span> Line! or pods! or listening and watching!</b> There is 
 plenty of space to participate at your comfort level\, and we will remind p
 eople at the dance not to assume anything about what someone else might be 
 comfortable with and to ask about and respect others' boundaries. Special w
 ristbands will be offered for people who want to indicate that they don't w
 ant to do neighbor swings or want to do two-hand turns in place of swings. 
 We want to be <i>even more</i> respectful than usual of individual boundari
 es and take nothing for granted about people's consent. </span><br><br><spa
 n>In the case of <b>rain</b>\, the dance will go on - if it's thundering\, 
 we will have to see (but come on out so we can figure it out together)!</sp
 an></span></span><br><br><span><span><b>No Zoom</b> - Unfortunately\, the b
 est venues we've found for in-person\, outdoor\, covered\, spacious events 
 do not work well for using internet.</span></span><br><br><span><span>Previ
 ously\, <b>bathrooms </b>were available at the nearby baseball field. We ar
 e not sure if they will be available every week.</span></span><br><br><span
 ><span><br><span><b>TONS OF FUN AND HAPPINESS • MUST BE VACCINATED AND BECO
 ME A MEMBER&nbsp\; </b></span></span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210715T224024Z
