DESCRIPTION:<br><span><span><strong><span>Contra</span> Dance <span>Skills<
 /span> FREE <span>Workshop</span> <br>Calling all dancers!<br>THERE WILL BE
  SNACKS</strong></span></span><br> <span><span>The Bloomington Old Time Mus
 ic &amp\; Dance Group will be offering a <span>Contra</span> Dance <span>Sk
 ills</span> <span>Workshop</span> on Monday\, February 23\, at Harmony Scho
 ol\, from 6:30-8:30 p.m. This <span>workshop</span> will offer insights int
 o many aspects of <span>contra</span> dance\, from frame and posture to giv
 ing weight and tension to broadening understanding of complex figures\, whi
 le also adding flourishes to enhance one's dancing. Concepts that we examin
 e will be placed into the context of actual dances\, to help dancers better
  understand their relevance. </span>Dancers of all levels are welcome and e
 ncouraged to attend: whether you're new to <span>contra</span> dance or hav
 e years of experience\, you'll find opportunities to gain insights\, connec
 t with others\, and have fun<span>. The <span>workshop</span> is free\, but
  <strong>we encourage preregistration to help us plan\, also for snacks</st
 rong>. So please\, preregister!</span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T024609Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Contra Skills Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
