DESCRIPTION:<strong>NOTE that this particular dance is at Serendipity (201 
 S College Ave)\, not Harmony School! </strong><br><strong><br></strong><br>
 <strong>About Our Dances</strong><ul><li><strong>Time: </strong>7:30-9:30 p
 .m.</li>   <li><strong>Location</strong>: Harmony School\, 909 E 2nd St\, B
 loomington\, IN\, 47401</li>   <li><strong>Entrance fee</strong>: by slidin
 g scale donation\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that ever
 yone will give at least something because the event is sustained by the com
 munity. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would break even
  after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be made <a h
 ref="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082b
 e7e5f22020734e68&id=298b3f55c0&e=6f029e4d69"><u><b><u>online</u></b></u></a
 > or at the door. </li>   <li><strong>Striving Toward Safe Space Policy</st
 rong>: We hope to create a dance in which everyone feels safe and welcome. 
 Please take a moment to review our <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.
 list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=5d4959b742&e=6f0
 29e4d69"><u><b><u>policy</u></b></u></a> on respect and consent.</li></ul><
 strong>Covid Policies</strong>   <br><ul><li><strong>Membership Requirement
 </strong>: Becoming a member is easy! As of July 1\, 2023\, membership is n
 ow optional for all our dances. Becoming a member is easy!</li><li>   1) Fi
 ll out a membership form at the dance.<br>   2) Pay $10 either at the dance
  or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0
 c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=92fa0d4267&e=6f029e4d69"><u><b><u>online</u></b
 ></u></a> (free for those 15 and under). </li>   <li><strong>Vaccination Re
 quirements</strong>: As of May 31\, 2023\, we are no longer requiring proof
  of vaccination.</li>   <li><strong>Masks Encouraged</strong>: Masks are re
 quired if you have been exposed to COVID recently.</li>   <li><strong>Stay 
 home if you...</strong>    <ul>       <li>have symptoms of COVID (which cou
 ld also mean cold or flu symptoms)\, regardless of whether or not you teste
 d for COVID</li>       <li>first tested positive for COVID within the last 
 5 days\, even without symptoms </li>       <li>first tested positive for CO
 VID more than 5 days ago and still have a fever\, and/or your symptoms are 
 not yet getting better</li>  <br></ul></li><li><strong>Exercise caution and
  wear a mask if... </strong>    <ul>       <li>you have been exposed to som
 eone who has tested positive (spent more than 15 minutes less than 6 feet a
 way from them\, without masks on\, indoors\, or spent 20 minutes or more in
  intense conversation or close proximity even outdoors\, without masks on) 
        <ul>           <li>err on the conservative side</li>           <li>w
 atch yourself for symptoms</li>           <li>take a COVID test on day 5 </
 li></ul></li>       <li>If the exposure happened within 5 days of the dance
 \, it is probably wisest to stay home then\, too\, until you have a chance 
 to test yourself. Please note that this is more conservative than the CDC's
  guidelines at this point.</li></ul></li>   <li><strong>Notify us if...</st
 rong><strong> </strong>   <ul>       <li>you are diagnosed with COVID-19 wi
 thin 10 days of attending any BOTMDG event\, please let the board know\, at
  <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><u><b><u>communicati
 ons@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></u></a>\, within 24 hours of your 
 diagnosis if you possibly can\, so that we can inform others.</li></ul></li
 ></ul>
