DESCRIPTION: <span><span><span><strong>About Our Dances</strong></span></sp
 an></span><ul><li><span><span><strong>Time: </strong>7:30-9:30 p.m.</span><
 /span></li>    <li><span><span><strong>Location</strong>: Harmony School\, 
 909 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47401</span></span></li>    <li><span><span
 ><strong>Entrance fee</strong>: by sliding scale donation\, with a suggeste
 d range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least something 
 because the event is sustained by the community. We estimate that if everyo
 ne were to give $10\, we would break even after paying the rental fee and t
 he performers. Donations may be made <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us1
 3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=298b3f55c
 0&amp\;e=6f029e4d69"><b><u>online</u></b></a> or at the door. </span></span
 ></li>    <li><span><span><strong>Striving Toward Safe Space Policy</strong
 >: We hope to create a dance in which everyone feels safe and welcome. Plea
 se take a moment to review our <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list
 -manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=5d4959b742&amp\
 ;e=6f029e4d69"><b><u>policy</u></b></a> on respect and consent.</span></spa
 n></li></ul><span> <span><span><strong>Covid Policies</strong></span></span
 ></span>   <br /><ul><li><span><span><strong>Membership Requirement</strong
 >: Becoming a member is easy! Membership is optional the first two times so
 meone attends the dance in 2023.<br />    1) Fill <span>out a membership fo
 rm at the dance.<br />    2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span
 ><a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications
 @<wbr />bloomingtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance.<b
 r />    3) Pay $10 either at the dance or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontr
 a.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=92fa
 0d4267&amp\;e=6f029e4d69"><b><u>online</u></b></a> (free for those 15 and u
 nder). </span></span></span></li>    <li><span><strong>Up-to-Date Vaccinati
 on Requirement</strong>: </span><span>All attendees (dancers\, musicians\, 
 callers\, observers) are required to have the most up-to-date COVID vaccine
  they are eligible for. Attendees may bring their most recent vaccine card 
 to the dance or email a copy of it to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomi
 ngtoncontra.org">communications@<wbr />bloomingtoncontra.org</a> by Tuesday
  night before the dance. (For most vaccinated people\, this means a bivalen
 t booster after September 2 or having had COVID within the past 90 days.)</
 span></li>    <li><span><strong><span>Masks Encouraged</span></strong><span
 >: Additionally\, masks are required if you have been exposed to COVID rece
 ntly.</span></span></li>    <li><span><span><span><strong>Stay home if you.
 ..</strong> </span></span></span>    <ul>        <li><span><span>have sympt
 oms of COVID (which could also mean cold or flu symptoms)\, regardless of w
 hether or not you tested for COVID</span></span></li>        <li><span><spa
 n>first tested positive for COVID within the last 5 days\, even without sym
 ptoms</span></span> </li>        <li><span><span>first tested positive for 
 COVID more than 5 days ago and still have a fever\, and/or your symptoms ar
 e not yet getting better</span></span></li>  <br /></ul></li><li><span><spa
 n><span><strong>Exercise caution and wear a mask if... </strong> </span></s
 pan></span>    <ul>        <li><span><span>you have been <span>exposed</spa
 n> to someone who has tested positive (spent more than 15 minutes less than
  6 feet away from them\, without masks on\, indoors\, or spent 20 minutes o
 r more in intense conversation or close proximity even outdoors\, without m
 asks on)</span></span>        <ul>            <li><span><span>err on the co
 nservative side</span></span></li>            <li><span><span>watch yoursel
 f for symptoms</span></span></li>            <li><span><span>take a COVID t
 est on day 5 </span></span></li></ul></li>        <li><span><span>If the <s
 pan>exposure</span> happened within 5 days of the dance\, it is probably wi
 sest to stay home then\, too\, until you have a chance to test yourself. Pl
 ease note that this is more conservative than the CDC's guidelines at this 
 point.</span></span></li></ul></li>    <li><span><span><span><strong>Notify
  us if...</strong></span></span></span><strong> </strong>    <ul>        <l
 i><span><span>you are diagnosed with COVID-19 within 10 days of attending a
 ny BOTMDG event\, please let the board know\, at <a href="mailto:communicat
 ions@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<wbr />bloomingtoncontra.o
 rg</u></b></a>\, within 24 hours of your diagnosis if you possibly can\, so
  that we can inform others.</span></span></li>    </ul>    </li></ul>
