UID:3cduo1g8unmjq79d00lh1tua5k@google.com
CREATED:20220413T172500Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><span><span>Special contra dance with the band Eupho
 r (</span></span>Tom Turino on banjo\, fiddle and vocals\; Matt Turino on f
 iddle\, guitar and feet\; Sam Payne on guitar\; and Michael Valliant on upr
 ight bass)! Euphor blends classic old-time tunes with the band’s compositio
 ns in creative\, percussive and improvisational ways to compel everyone to 
 dance!&nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;<br>Meg Dedolph is a Chicago-area dance caller with
  a deeply weird repertoire\, which allows her to call contra dances for roo
 ms full of enthusiasts and newcomers\, to teach Irish set dances at Morris 
 dance weekends or to call a night of unplanned triplets during a snowstorm.
  She is a regular caller at her home dance series as well as at church harv
 est festivals and weddings\, and she and her partner plan to resume running
  their all-ages barn dance series as soon as current events permit. Her wal
 kthroughs are fast and concise\, she is sometimes funny\, and she just want
 s everyone to have a good time.<br>&nbsp\;<br>Entrance is by donation for B
 OTMDG members\, or $12 for non-members (with the option of becoming a membe
 r).<span><span></span><span> Covid-related protocols will remain the same f
 or this dance - proof of up-to-date vaccination required\; masks required.&
 nbsp\;</span></span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></
 span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span>Harmony School <br></span></spa
 n></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220413T172635Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Special Saturday Contra Dance - Euphor and caller Meg Dedolph
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
