CREATED:20221205T194556Z
DESCRIPTION:<strong>2023 Policies and Changes</strong><br>The following cha
 nges were approved by the BOTMDG board during its November meeting.<ul><li>
 <strong>Dance Time</strong>: Beginning January 4\, the dance will run from&
 nbsp\;<em>7:30-9:30 p.m.</em>&nbsp\;For the month of January\, there will b
 e a waltz midway through but no break. For the month of February\, there wi
 ll be a 5-minute break at 8:30 followed by a waltz. After that\, the board 
 will make a decision about whether or not to include a break.</li><li><stro
 ng>Vaccines</strong>: Beginning January 4\, all attendees (dancers\, musici
 ans\, callers\, observers) are&nbsp\;<em>required to have the bivalent boos
 ter</em>\, if eligible. Attendees may bring their most recent vaccine card 
 to the dance or email a copy of it to&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:communications@
 bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<wbr>bloomingtoncontra.org</u><
 /b></a>. (For most people ages 12 and older\, this means a booster after Se
 ptember 2 or having had COVID within the past 90 days.)</li><li><strong>Mas
 ks</strong>: Beginning January 4\,&nbsp\;<em>masks are encouraged but optio
 nal&nbsp\;</em>at BOTMDG dances.</li><li><strong>Membership</strong>:<ul><l
 i>Current memberships are valid through January 24. All who wish to vote in
  the January 25 annual member meeting must renew their membership by the 25
 th.</li><li>Beginning Wednesday\, January 4\, membership is optional the fi
 rst time someone attends the dance - first timers can pay for membership an
 d/or pay the sliding scale entrance fee.&nbsp\;<em>The second time someone 
 attends\, membership is required</em>.</li><li>The board will set membershi
 p fees at its December board meeting.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Entrance Fe
 e</strong>: No changes were made to the entrance fee. The entrance fee will
  continue as a&nbsp\;<em>sliding scale donation\, with a suggested range of
  $3-20</em>. Based on our average attendance\, we need to bring in approxim
 ately $10/person to break even.</li><li><strong>Additional COVID-19 Policie
 s</strong>: As of now\, our other COVID-19 policies regarding when to stay 
 home from the dance\, what to do if you are exposed\, and when to notify th
 e board of illness will remain in place. The board will revisit these polic
 ies at the December meeting.</li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230101T152054Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Open Mic Night - band led by Danny Weddle\, Teri Klassen\, and Kyla
  Wargel
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
