DESCRIPTION:<span>Fiddler Tom Cunningham of Louisville takes a break from h
 is Virtual World Tour to bring us waltzes\, bluegrass\, and tunes from all 
 over. Joining Tom will be Chet Gray\, also of Louisville\, calling dances f
 or 1–2 dancers.&nbsp\; <span></span></span><span><span></span></span><br><s
 pan><span><span>&nbsp\; <span><br><span>---------- </span><br>&nbsp\;<br><s
 pan><span><span>If you'd like the Zoom link\, please email us at <span><spa
 n>at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@b
 loomingtoncontra.org</a></span></span>.</span></span></span><br><span><span
 ><span>As of March\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begin at <b>8 p.m. Eastern
 </b>.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you haven’t b
 een to one of our online events\, you might be wondering what to expect! As
  our musicians play for us\, and the caller calls\, you are welcome to danc
 e with us in your own space\, play along with the musicians with your mic m
 uted\, or just watch and listen. We also try to check in with everyone brie
 fly each week. The music lasts until about 8:45\, followed by the check-in.
 </span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>Waltzes are easy to d
 ance alone or with a partner. Up-tempo tunes will sometimes have <span>cont
 ra</span>-like calling\, but for the times when there is no calling\, pleas
 e feel free to dance along at home with <span>contra</span> moves of your c
 hoice. Or just boogie down to the amazing music!</span></span>&nbsp\; </spa
 n><br><br><span>----------</span><span><br></span><br><span>We are grateful
  for all donations\, and happy to be able to keep paying our musicians and 
 dance leaders during these unusual times. You can find our <a href="http://
 bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/"
 >PayPal donation button on our website</a>.&nbsp\; </span></span></span></s
 pan></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210226T222408Z
