DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u>Join us for our weekly Wednesday night
  contra dance!<br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance In
 formation</b></span></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.<br></span
 ></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Beginner lesson at 7:10 p.m. (
 try to arrive by 7 to register as a member)<br></span></span></li> &nbsp\; 
 &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><li><span><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and mask
 s required (see more details below)</span></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><
 span><span>Entrance fee by donation after becoming a member (suggested rang
 e is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></li></
 ul><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Details</b></span><br><b>Up-
 to-date vaccination is required</b>. This means that if your 2nd dose of a 
 Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</span> was at least 5 months ago or your si
 ngle dose of a Johnson &amp\; Johnson <span>vaccine</span> was at least 2 m
 onths ago\, you will need to show us evidence of a booster shot. (For our p
 urposes\, even if you are eligible for more than one booster shot\, only on
 e is required.) If we have not yet seen proof of your most recent vaccinati
 on\, please send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontr
 a.org"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by the
  end of Tuesday\, or bring the card or a photo of it with you to the dance.
 <b><i> </i></b>Thank you for helping to keep us all safe!</span><br><br><sp
 an><b>Membership is required.</b> Becoming a member is easy!&nbsp\;</span><
 /span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span>1) Fill <span>in a membership 
 form at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/uploa
 ds/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf"><b><u>print one</u></b></a> to comple
 te in advance.&nbsp\;</span></span></span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span>
 <span><span>2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a href="mail
 to:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomi
 ngtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance.&nbsp\;</span></
 span></span></html-blob><br><html-blob><span><span><span>3) Pay $12 either 
 at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/"><b>
 <u>online</u></b></a> ($2 for those under 30). </span><br><br><b>Masks are 
 required. </b>Masks must cover the mouth and nose at all times in the dance
  hall and when entering the building. Dancers can step outside the dance ha
 ll to drink water. <br><br><b>This dance is run by donation</b>\, with a su
 ggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least some
 thing because the event is sustained by the community. We estimate that if 
 everyone were to give $10\, we would break even after paying the rental fee
  and the performers. Donations may be made <a href="http://bloomingtoncontr
 a.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/"><b><u>online</u
 ></b></a> or at the door.</span></span>&nbsp\;<u></u><u></u></html-blob>
