DESCRIPTION:<span>The Cosmic Otters make people dance. They start with a so
 lid rhythmic foundation of guitar and piano\, add inventive fiddle/accordio
 n harmonies\, and finish with tasteful percussion.  Katie Zukof calls old f
 avorites and new Zoom contras written for 1 and 2 dancers.</span><br><span>
 <span>&nbsp\;<br><span>---------- </span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>I
 f you'd like the Zoom link\, please email us at <span><span>at <a href="mai
 lto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@bloomingtoncontra.
 org</a></span></span>.</span></span></span><br><span><span><span>As of Marc
 h\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begin at <b>8 p.m. Eastern</b>.</span></spa
 n></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you haven’t been to one of our
  online events\, you might be wondering what to expect! As our musicians pl
 ay for us\, and the caller calls\, you are welcome to dance with us in your
  own space\, play along with the musicians with your mic muted\, or just wa
 tch and listen. We also try to check in with everyone briefly each week. Th
 e music lasts until about 8:45\, followed by the check-in.</span></span></s
 pan><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>Waltzes are easy to dance alone or wit
 h a partner. Up-tempo tunes will sometimes have <span>contra</span>-like ca
 lling\, but for the times when there is no calling\, please feel free to da
 nce along at home with <span>contra</span> moves of your choice. Or just bo
 ogie down to the amazing music!</span></span>&nbsp\; </span><br><br><span>-
 ---------</span><span><br></span><br><span>We are grateful for all donation
 s\, and happy to be able to keep paying our musicians and dance leaders dur
 ing these unusual times. You can find our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra
 .org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">PayPal donation 
 button on our website</a>.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; </span></span><br></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210226T222421Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Zoom Event: The Cosmic Otters (Meg Dedolph\, Eric Schedler\, Jonath
 an Whitall) with Katie Zukof calling
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
