DESCRIPTION:<strong>About Our Dances</strong><ul><li><strong>Time: </strong
 >7:30-9:30 p.m.</li>   <li><strong>Location</strong>: Harmony School\, 909 
 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47401</li>   <li><strong>Entrance fee</strong>:
  by sliding scale donation\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope
  that everyone will give at least something because the event is sustained 
 by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would 
 break even after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be
  made <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.
 list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D0c065082be7e5f22020734e68%26id%3D298b3f55c0
 %26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1678199111023990&
 amp\;usg=AOvVaw1ACP7--bu__wRFmAoXUqeb" target="_blank"><u><b><u>online</u><
 /b></u></a> or at the door. </li>   <li><strong>Striving Toward Safe Space 
 Policy</strong>: We hope to create a dance in which everyone feels safe and
  welcome. Please take a moment to review our <a href="https://www.google.co
 m/url?q=https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D0c06
 5082be7e5f22020734e68%26id%3D5d4959b742%26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=D&amp\;sou
 rce=calendar&amp\;ust=1678199111023990&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2cd7LGlLN_lqBRObRSV3o
 y" target="_blank"><u><b><u>policy</u></b></u></a> on respect and consent.<
 /li></ul><strong>Covid Policies</strong>   <br><ul><li><strong>Membership R
 equirement</strong>: Becoming a member is easy! Membership is optional the 
 first two times someone attends the dance in 2023.<br>   1) Fill out a memb
 ership form at the dance.<br>   2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to 
 <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org" target="_blank"><u><b
 ><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org </u></b></u></a>or bring it
  to the dance.<br>   3) Pay $10 either at the dance or <a href="https://www
 .google.com/url?q=https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/clic
 k?u%3D0c065082be7e5f22020734e68%26id%3D92fa0d4267%26e%3D6f029e4d69&amp\;sa=
 D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1678199111023990&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2a87EoZjAqK
 A7QZ0KYD6iW" target="_blank"><u><b><u>online</u></b></u></a> (free for thos
 e 15 and under). </li>   <li><strong>Up-to-Date Vaccination Requirement</st
 rong>: All attendees (dancers\, musicians\, callers\, observers) are requir
 ed to have the most up-to-date COVID vaccine they are eligible for. Attende
 es may bring their most recent vaccine card to the dance or email a copy of
  it to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org" target="_blank
 "><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></a> by Tuesday night b
 efore the dance. (For most vaccinated people\, this means a bivalent booste
 r after September 2 or having had COVID within the past 90 days.)</li>   <l
 i><strong>Masks Encouraged</strong>: Additionally\, masks are required if y
 ou have been exposed to COVID recently.</li>   <li><strong>Stay home if you
 ...</strong>    <ul>       <li>have symptoms of COVID (which could also mea
 n cold or flu symptoms)\, regardless of whether or not you tested for COVID
 </li>       <li>first tested positive for COVID within the last 5 days\, ev
 en without symptoms </li>       <li>first tested positive for COVID more th
 an 5 days ago and still have a fever\, and/or your symptoms are not yet get
 ting better</li>  <br></ul></li><li><strong>Exercise caution and wear a mas
 k if... </strong>    <ul>       <li>you have been exposed to someone who ha
 s tested positive (spent more than 15 minutes less than 6 feet away from th
 em\, without masks on\, indoors\, or spent 20 minutes or more in intense co
 nversation or close proximity even outdoors\, without masks on)        <ul>
            <li>err on the conservative side</li>           <li>watch yourse
 lf for symptoms</li>           <li>take a COVID test on day 5 </li></ul></l
 i>       <li>If the exposure happened within 5 days of the dance\, it is pr
 obably wisest to stay home then\, too\, until you have a chance to test you
 rself. Please note that this is more conservative than the CDC&#39\;s guide
 lines at this point.</li></ul></li>   <li><strong>Notify us if...</strong><
 strong> </strong>   <ul>       <li>you are diagnosed with COVID-19 within 1
 0 days of attending any BOTMDG event\, please let the board know\, at <a hr
 ef="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org" target="_blank"><u><b><u>c
 ommunications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></u></a>\, within 24 hour
 s of your diagnosis if you possibly can\, so that we can inform others.</li
 ></ul></li></ul>
