 ><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and masks required (see more details below)<
 /span></span></li><li><span><span>Entrance fee by donation (suggested range
  is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></li></u
 l></span></span><strong><span><span> <span><span><span><strong>Weekly Wedne
 sday Dance Details</strong></span><br /><strong>Up-to-date vaccination is r
 equired</strong>. </span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><s
 pan>This means that if your 2nd dose of a Pfizer or Moderna <span>vaccine</
 span> was at least 5 months ago or your single dose of a Johnson &amp\; Joh
 nson <span>vaccine</span> was at least 2 months ago\, you will need to show
  us evidence of a booster shot. (For our purposes\, even if you are eligibl
 e for more than one booster shot\, only one is required.) If we have not ye
 t seen proof of your most recent vaccination\, please send a photo to <a hr
 ef="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@bloom
 ingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by the end of Tuesday\, or bring the card or a
  photo of it with you to the dance.<em> </em>Thank you for helping to keep 
 us all safe!</span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><br /><br
  /><span><strong>Membership is required.</strong> </span></span></span></sp
 an></strong><span><span><span><span>Becoming a member is easy! 1) Fill <spa
 n>in a membership form at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.or
 g/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf">print one</a> to co
 mplete in advance. 2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a hre
 f="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@bloomi
 ngtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance. 3) Pay $12 eith
 er at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/">
 online</a> ($2 for those under 30). </span></span></span></span></span><str
 ong><span><span><span><span><br /><br /><strong>Masks are required. </stron
 g></span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>Masks must c
 over the mouth and nose at all times. Dancers can step outside for a mask b
 reak or may step into the hallway to take a drink of water.</span></span></
 span></span><strong><span><span><span><span><br /><br /><strong>This dance 
 is run by donation</strong>\,</span></span></span></span></strong><span><sp
 an><span><span> with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyon
 e will give at least something because the event is sustained by the commun
 ity. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would break even af
 ter paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be made <a href
 ="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-d
 owntime/">online</a> or at the door.</span></span></span>  </span><strong><
 span><br /></span></strong></span></span></span><br /><span><span><span><st
 rong><span> </span></strong></span></span></span><br /><span><span><span><s
 trong><span>Beginner Dance Lesson Every Week</span></strong></span><br /><s
 pan>New</span> and <span>beginner</span> dancers are welcome to become memb
 ers and dance with us! New dancers should try to arrive at 7 p.m. to check 
 in at the welcome table. A beginner lesson will be offered by the caller ev
 ery week at 7:10 p.m. before the dance. Invite a friend!<br /><br /><span><
 strong><span>Plan for the Weather - water\, extra shirts\, sweat towels</sp
 an></strong></span><br /><span>As it warms up\, please keep in mind that th
 e Harmony School gym does not have air conditioning. Dancers are encouraged
  to bring a water bottle to stay hydrated\, as well as sweat towels to use 
 and extra shirts to change into</span> as needed.<br /><br /><span><strong>
 <span>Striving Toward Safe Space</span></strong></span><br />We hope to cre
 ate a dance in which everyone feels safe and welcome. Please take a moment 
 to review our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/Safe-Space-Policy.pdf">
 policy</a> on respect and consent.</span></span><span><br /></span><span><s
 pan></span></span>
