UID:2154lp0v973rifnm8jubrjm2fg_R20220106T003000@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20220105T193000
CREATED:20211028T145844Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span><span><strong>Weekly Dance Information</strong></sp
 an></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.</span></span></li><li><spa
 n><span>Harmony School (909 E 2nd St\, Bloomington)</span></span></li><li><
 span><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and masks required (see more details bel
 ow)</span></span></li><li><span><span>Entrance fee by donation (suggested r
 ange is $3-20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></li
 ></ul><span><span><span><strong><span>Beginner Dance Lesson Every Week</spa
 n></strong></span><br><span>New</span> and <span>beginner</span> dancers ar
 e welcome to become members and dance with us! New dancers should try to ar
 rive at 7 p.m. to check in at the welcome table. A beginner lesson will be 
 offered by the caller every week at 7:10 p.m. before the dance. </span></sp
 an><br><br><span><span><span><strong>Weekly Dance Details</strong></span><b
 r><strong>Full vaccination is required</strong> (meaning you have had every
  dose you qualify for). We will need to see your vaccination card\, if you 
 haven't already shared it with us. Either send a photo to <a href="mailto:c
 ommunications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@<wbr>bloomingtoncontra.
 org</a> by the end of Tuesday\, or bring it with you to the dance.<br><br><
 strong>Membership is required.</strong> Becoming a member is easy - you can
  do so online at&nbsp\;<a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.
 com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=3823d575eb&amp\;e=9fd49
 b8c10">http://bloomingtoncontra.<wbr>org/become-a-member/</a>\, or you can 
 bring money to the dance. Annual membership is $12 (or only $2 per year for
  those under 30).<br><br><strong>Masks are required. </strong>Masks must co
 ver the mouth and nose at all times. Dancers can step outside for a mask br
 eak or may step into the hallway to take a drink of water.<br><br>This danc
 e is run <strong>by donation</strong>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $
 20. We hope that everyone will give at least something because the event is
  sustained by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\
 , we would break even after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donat
 ions may be made <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performe
 rs-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">online</a> or at the door.</span></span>
