UID:7877fdnhj1k0ov0sgdukqfi871@google.com
CREATED:20210328T150043Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Tina Bergmann &amp\; Bryan Thomas are a northeast Ohio hu
 sband and wife duo playing American Old Time\, Celtic and South American Mu
 sic on Hammered Dulcimer &amp\; Bass. Tina is a virtuoso hammered dulcimer 
 player known for her driving energy\, syncopated rhythms and fine musicalit
 y. Described by Pete Seeger as “the best hammered dulcimer player I’ve hear
 d in my life\,” she’s also been promoted as the “Diva of the Dulcimer” by A
 pollo’s Fire\, Cleveland’s Baroque Orchestra. Bryan Thomas is a dynamic and
  conversational double bassist\, sought for his ability to embrace traditio
 n but defy convention. Together Tina and Bryan create a surprising and wond
 erful musical experience that has enthralled audiences throughout the Unite
 d States.</span><br><br><br><span><span><span><span><br><span>---------- </
 span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you'd like the Zoom link\, please 
 email us at <span><span>at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra
 .org">communications@bloomingtoncontra.org</a></span></span>.</span></span>
 </span><br><span><span><span>As of March\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begi
 n at <b>8 p.m. Eastern</b>.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span>
 <span>If you haven’t been to one of our online events\, you might be wonder
 ing what to expect! As our musicians play for us\, and the caller calls\, y
 ou are welcome to dance with us in your own space\, play along with the mus
 icians with your mic muted\, or just watch and listen. We also try to check
  in with everyone briefly each week. The music lasts until about 8:45\, fol
 lowed by the check-in.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span
 >Waltzes are easy to dance alone or with a partner. Up-tempo tunes will som
 etimes have <span>contra</span>-like calling\, but for the times when there
  is no calling\, please feel free to dance along at home with <span>contra<
 /span> moves of your choice. Or just boogie down to the amazing music!</spa
 n></span>&nbsp\; </span><br><br><span>----------</span><span><br></span><br
 ><span>We are grateful for all donations\, and happy to be able to keep pay
 ing our musicians and dance leaders during these unusual times. You can fin
 d our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-t
 he-covid-19-downtime/">PayPal donation button on our website</a>.&nbsp\;&nb
 sp\; </span></span></span></span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210328T150043Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hu$hmoney (Tina Bergmann\, hammered dulcimer and Bryan Thomas\, bas
 s) with Susan English (on Zoom)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
