CREATED:20220330T010639Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Please see our webpage for the latest informa
 tion: <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/events/50th-anniversary-celebra
 tion/">http://bloomingtoncontra.org/events/50th-anniversary-celebration/</a
 ><u></u><br><u></u>&nbsp\;<u></u><br><u></u><p>We’ve been dancing for 50 ye
 ars! Please come celebrate with us!</p><h4>Saturday\,&nbsp\;July 9\,&nbsp\;
 2022\, from&nbsp\;4pm&nbsp\;to&nbsp\;10pm</h4><h4>Mike’s Dance Barn\,&nbsp\
 ;2277&nbsp\;Indiana State Road&nbsp\;46\, Nashville\, IN 47448</h4><p><em>M
 ike’s Dance Barn is a beautiful summertime venue with a large wooden dance 
 floor\, air conditioning\, and a large parking lot\,&nbsp\;15 miles east of
 &nbsp\;Bloomington&nbsp\;and&nbsp\;4 miles west of&nbsp\;Nashville\,&nbsp\;
 Indiana.</em></p><p>Come hang out and enjoy dancing\, music\, and reminisci
 ng with old friends. We are excited to bring together dancers\, musicians\,
  and callers from the last 5 decades of our Wednesday night dance. Groups o
 f musicians and callers will trade off throughout the afternoon and evening
 . You are welcome to bring a pop-up tent and chairs for outdoor visiting an
 d jamming in the parking lot.</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><em>Note: EVERYONE MUST S
 END IN OR BRING PROOF OF COVID VACCINATION *AND* ONE BOOSTER – (if not yet 
 eligible for booster\, then full primary vaccination) – we cannot let you i
 n without this proof\, and we will be sad to send you away when you have co
 me so far. See more details below. Masks will be required on the dance floo
 r.</em></p><p>&nbsp\;</p><h3>EARLY-BIRD REGISTRATION DEADLINE SATURDAY\, JU
 LY 2 (online or by mail)</h3><p>1) Register</p><ul><li>Online: <a href="htt
 ps://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf8rDnaYlmstDftPHL7vZ6Sj5V9WOxdg-_JG-
 zK_LNACKUVMQ/viewform">Register here</a> (<em>must include proof of vaccina
 tion\; see details above</em>)</li><li>Paper registration available at Wedn
 esday dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/uploads/202
 2/06/flier-50th.pdf">download and print the paper registration form here</a
 >. Bring completed paper registration to Wednesday dance or mail (postmarke
 d by July 2) to BOTMDG\, PO Box 3238\, Bloomington\, IN 47402-3238 (<em>mus
 t include proof of vaccination\; see details above</em>).</li></ul><p>2) Se
 nd a photo or scan of your proof of vaccination and booster to <a>anniversa
 ry@bloomingtoncontra.org</a> (preferred)\, or bring proof to the dance.</p>
 <p>3) Pay registration fee <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/50th-anniv
 ersary-registration-and-payment/">here</a>.</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><strong>Ear
 ly-Bird Registration Fees</strong></p><p>General (over 12 years old): $15</
 p><p>Ages 5–12: $8</p><p>Under 5: Free</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><strong>Walk-In 
 Registration Fees</strong></p><p>(<em>Must bring proof of vaccination inclu
 ding booster if eligible\, please see details above – we do NOT want to sen
 d you away when you have come so far to dance with us</em>.)</p><p>General 
 (over 12 years old): $20</p><p>Ages 5–12: $10</p><p>Under 5: Free</p><p>&nb
 sp\;</p><h3><strong>COVID POLICIES: PLEASE READ!</strong></h3><p><strong>Ma
 sking:</strong> will be required for everyone on the dance floor at all tim
 es (whether dancing\, standing\, calling\, or anything else). Masking is op
 tional off the dance floor. Bandannas do not count as masks. (Mask policy s
 ubject to potential tightening depending on COVID situation in July.)</p><p
 ><strong>Vaccination: </strong>At time of registration\, we need proof of t
 he following:</p><p><strong><em>Full primary series of vaccine plus a boost
 er (if ineligible for booster because of age or timing of primary series\, 
 please let us know\, and provide proof of full primary series regardless).<
 /em></strong></p><p>If registering online or by early-bird mail\, send a ph
 oto of your vaccination card showing the above vaccinations and your name\,
  or a vaccination certificate from your state.</p><p>Walk-ins can bring you
 r Covid card\, a photocopy\, a photo on your phone\, or a vaccination certi
 ficate from your state.</p><p><strong><em>We really don’t want to have to t
 urn you away\, so please bring your proof of vaccination.</em></strong></p>
 <p><strong>&nbsp\;</strong></p><p><strong>Individual Cancellation Policy: <
 /strong>Please stay home if you test positive\, feel ill\, and/or may have 
 been exposed to Covid. If you have already registered but need to stay home
  for these reasons\, please contact us for a refund at <a>anniversary@bloom
 ingtoncontra.org</a>.</p><p><strong>&nbsp\;</strong></p><p><strong>Unlikely
  Cancellation of the Dance</strong>: We have all learned to live with uncer
 tainty over the last couple of years. In the unlikely event we have to canc
 el the entire event due to COVID\, we regret we will not be able to refund 
 registration fees. We have worked hard to make the fees as low as possible<
 /p><h3></h3><h3>INFORMAL FRIDAY HANGOUT</h3><p>You are also welcome to join
  us for an informal gathering&nbsp\;<span dir="ltr">on&nbsp\;</span><span d
 ir="ltr">Friday\, July&nbsp\;</span><span dir="ltr">8\, 6:30-8:30 p.m.</spa
 n> at the Rev. Ernie Butler Park\,&nbsp\;<span dir="ltr">812 West 9</span><
 span dir="ltr">th</span><span dir="ltr">&nbsp\;Street\, Bloomington\, IN 47
 404</span>. Pizza while it lasts\, BYOB\, bring a dish to share\, and bring
  your instruments &amp\; chairs to join in on music jams!</p><p>This can al
 so be a chance for musicians to figure out band configurations for the foll
 owing day.</p><h3></h3><h3>50th ANNIVERSARY CELEBRATION SCHEDULE&nbsp\;AND 
 INFO</h3><ul><li>4 pm&nbsp\;– Check-in &amp\; Walk-in registration begin</l
 i><li>6 sets of music between 4 and 10 p.m.<ul><li>Brad Leftwich of the Hum
 dingers\, with Linda Higginbotham\, Sam Bartlett\, Abby Ladin – all from Bl
 oomington</li><li>Brian “Hawk” Hubbard – from Florida and David Molk – from
  California – formerly with the ‘70s Dry and Dusty Stringband</li><li>Rick 
 Martin of the Troublesome Creek Stringband – from Virginia</li><li>Paul Tyl
 er of the Volo Bogtrotters Stringband – from Chicago</li><li>Frank Hall – f
 rom Ireland &amp\; Bob Herring – from Virginia\, Fiddlers – with Teri Klass
 en of Bloomington on guitar – all formerly with the ‘70s -‘<span dir="ltr">
 80s Easy Street&nbsp\;Band</span></li><li>OPEN MIC led by Tamara Loewenthal
  will be the third set: <span dir="ltr">6-7 p.m. – all musicians are welcom
 e to join on stage!</span></li></ul></li><li>Snacks provided by BOTMDG / Pl
 ease bring your own water bottle to fill from dispenser</li><li>Mike’s Danc
 e Barn pub-style food and drinks available for sale:<ul><li>$7–$9 —&nbsp\;S
 andwich/Fries Combo options: Hamburgers\, Fish\, Chicken\, Tenderloin\, BBQ
 </li><li>$3 — Bowl of Mike’s “Kick Butt” Beans –&nbsp\;Veg or Meat options<
 /li><li>$2–$5&nbsp\;— Soft drinks\, fruit-flavored waters\, domestic &amp\;
  imported beer &amp\; wine</li></ul></li><li>9:45 pm&nbsp\;– Final waltz</l
 i><li>10:00 pm&nbsp\;– Music and dancing end</li></ul><p>&nbsp\;</p><p>Info
 rmal Bloomington gatherings may happen Saturday night (following the 50th a
 nniversary celebration) and Sunday afternoon. Watch for more information cl
 oser to the time.</p><h3></h3><h3>OTHER MUSICIANS</h3><p>These folks will a
 lso be available play music for the event.</p><p>* Sam Bartlett\, Abby Ladi
 n\, Teri Klassen\,&nbsp\;Tamara Loewenthal\, Eric Schedler\,&nbsp\;Rob&nbsp
 \;Fischman\,&nbsp\;Andy&nbsp\;K<wbr>nust\,&nbsp\;Jack Laskey\, Michael Vall
 iant\, and many others… &nbsp\;Let us know if you’d like to join in too!</p
 ><h3></h3><h3>CALLERS</h3><p>*&nbsp\;Bill Meek of Chicago</p><p>*&nbsp\;Rog
 er Diggle&nbsp\;of Wisconsin</p><p>* Paul Tyler of Chicago</p><p>* Tamara&n
 bsp\;Loewenthal of Bloomington</p><p>* OTHERS CALLING: &nbsp\;Mary Beth&nbs
 p\;Roska\,&nbsp\;Mark Richardson\, Katie Zukof\, Bill Baus\,&nbsp\;Kyla War
 gel\,&nbsp\;Tammy&nbsp\;Berhman\,&nbsp\;Mercury McGill\, Patrick Blackstone
  – all from Bloomington.<br>Others from near and far are also welcome. Let 
 us know if you’re interested!!</p><p><em>Preliminary positive responses to 
 attend the 50th from far-flung dance group veterans include caller and musi
 cian Frank Hall of Ireland and caller Dillon Bustin of Massachusetts (if he
 alth permits)\; caller Bill Meek and caller/fiddler Paul Tyler of Chicago\;
  caller Roger Diggle of Wisconsin\; Dry and Dusty String Band’s Brian “Hawk
 ” Hubbard of Florida and David Molk of California\; and Easy Street String 
 Band’s Bob Herri
LAST-MODIFIED:20220702T182253Z
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:50th Anniversary Celebration
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
