UID:00th39pll1noqmpd65fb5fk9e8@google.com
CREATED:20210328T145446Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Peregrine Road features two seasoned and versatile musici
 ans are known together as a power duo capable of an incredible range of sty
 les. Join Karen Axelrod and Rachel Bell for an evening of energetic Celtic 
 reels\, heartbreakingly beautiful waltzes\, mesmerizing French dance tunes\
 , lively improvisations\, sweet jigs\, and more. Self-described "dance mani
 ac\," Wendy Graham’s passion for music\, song and dance caught fire on a 19
 91 youth dance tour of Denmark. Pre-Pandemic\, Wendy led English\, American
 \, Community\, and couples dance (Frankie Manning’s Lindy Hop\, Latin dance
 \, and more) in her hometown\, Durango\, Colorado\, throughout the country 
 as far away as Alaska\, and abroad in England and Denmark. These days\, she
  can be found calling virtual dances for dancers from around the world. She
  proudly served on the Country Dance and Song Society (CDSS) board\, is a L
 ifetime Contribution Award committee member\, and the Partner Affiliate Amb
 assador for the Southwest. She currently serves on the Lloyd Shaw Foundatio
 n board.</span><br><span>&nbsp\;<span><span><span> <br><span>---------- </s
 pan><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you'd like the Zoom link\, please e
 mail us at <span><span>at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.
 org">communications@bloomingtoncontra.org</a></span></span>.</span></span><
 /span><br><span><span><span>As of March\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begin
  at <b>8 p.m. Eastern</b>.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><
 span>If you haven’t been to one of our online events\, you might be wonderi
 ng what to expect! As our musicians play for us\, and the caller calls\, yo
 u are welcome to dance with us in your own space\, play along with the musi
 cians with your mic muted\, or just watch and listen. We also try to check 
 in with everyone briefly each week. The music lasts until about 8:45\, foll
 owed by the check-in.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>
 Waltzes are easy to dance alone or with a partner. Up-tempo tunes will some
 times have <span>contra</span>-like calling\, but for the times when there 
 is no calling\, please feel free to dance along at home with <span>contra</
 span> moves of your choice. Or just boogie down to the amazing music!</span
 ></span>&nbsp\; </span><br><br><span>----------</span><span><br></span><br>
 <span>We are grateful for all donations\, and happy to be able to keep payi
 ng our musicians and dance leaders during these unusual times. You can find
  our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-th
 e-covid-19-downtime/">PayPal donation button on our website</a>.&nbsp\;&nbs
 p\;&nbsp\; </span></span></span></span><br></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210328T150927Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Peregrine Road (Rachel Bell\, accordion\, and Karen Axelrod\, piano
  and accordion) with caller Wendy Graham (on Zoom)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
