DESCRIPTION:On Sunday\, November 5\, from 4–6 PM in Room 1B at the downtown
  branch of the Monroe County Public Library\, members of the newly formed B
 OTMDG dance etiquette committee will host a town hall discussion about what
  makes a safe\, comfortable\, happy\, welcoming\, and fun dance.  Please jo
 in us for light refreshments and to discuss the shared expectations of our 
 dance community.  We’d like to hear from as many people as possible—we beli
 eve that being on the same page about dance floor expectations is one of th
 e most important factors to keeping our dance community thriving!
LAST-MODIFIED:20231101T184535Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Dance Etiquette Discussion (MCPL 1B)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
