DESCRIPTION:Contra and waltzes with Tina Bergmann on hammered dulcimer\, Br
 yan Thomas on bass\, and calling by Susan English. Coming to us from Northe
 astern Ohio\, Tina and Bryan are a husband and wife duo playing American Ol
 d Time\, Celtic and South American Music. Tina is a virtuoso hammered dulci
 mer player known for her driving energy\, syncopated rhythms and fine music
 ality whom Pete Seeger called “the best hammered dulcimer player I’ve heard
  in my life.” Bryan is a dynamic and conversational double bassist\, sought
  for his ability to embrace tradition but defy convention. https://www.allr
 oadsleadhome.com/tina-with-bryan-thomas<br>Susan\, who called a wonderful d
 ance for us in October\, is steeped in teaching and dance of all kinds and 
 pulls it all together for a happy and high-energy evening of contra. https:
 //www.woosterdance.com/susan-english<br><br><font><span>Join us using your 
 computer or mobile device&nbsp\;for fellowship\, music\, and even some virt
 ual dancing while we deal with the restrictions due to the COVID-19 pandemi
 c.&nbsp\; See our Email newsletter for details or contact <span><a href="ma
 ilto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@bloomingtoncontra
 .org</a></span><span></span></span></font><br><font><span><span></span></sp
 an></font>
