 )\, with Tamara Loewenthal calling&nbsp\; </span></span><br></strong></span
 ></span></span><br><span><span><span><strong>&nbsp\;</strong></span></span>
 </span><br><span><span><span><strong>Wednesday Night Dance Details</strong>
 </span><br><span><strong>Vaccines are required</strong>.&nbsp\;We will need
  to see your vaccination card\, if you haven't already shared it with us. E
 ither send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"
 >communications@<wbr>bloomingtoncontra.org</a> by the end of Tuesday\, or b
 ring it with you to the dance. </span><br><br>This is a <strong>members-onl
 y</strong> dance. Becoming a member is easy - <span>you can do so online at
 &nbsp\;<a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?
 u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=ffafc37ce6&amp\;e=aa19521646">http://bl
 oomingtoncontra.<wbr>org/become-a-member/</a>\, or you can bring $12 to the
  dance. Note: membership for anyone under 30 years old is only $2!</span><b
 r><br><span>Dances begin at <strong>7:30 p.m. Eastern</strong>. </span>The 
 last waltz will conclude by 8:45 p.m. to allow time for cleanup. You are we
 lcome to come early to help set up or stay late to help pack up.<br><br>Eve
 nts will be in-person at the Big Shelter at <strong>Marci Jane Lewis Park</
 strong>\, 106 South Park Street\, in Ellettsville - just 15 minutes from do
 wntown Bloomington!<strong> </strong></span></span><br><br><span><span><spa
 n>This dance is run <strong>by donation</strong>\, with a suggested range f
 rom $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least something\, even if
  it's very little\, because the event is sustained by the community. We wil
 l continue to give 100% of the donations to the performers.</span> <span>Do
 nations may be made in person or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.li
 st-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=067fffa0b5&am
 p\;e=aa19521646">here</a>.</span><br><br><span><strong><span>Contra</span> 
 Line! or pods! or listening and watching!</strong> There is plenty of space
  to participate at your comfort level\, and we will remind people at the da
 nce not to assume anything about what someone else might be comfortable wit
 h and to ask about and respect others' boundaries. Special wristbands will 
 be offered for people who want to indicate that they don't want to do neigh
 bor swings or want to do two-hand turns in place of swings. We want to be <
 em>even more</em> respectful than usual of individual boundaries and take n
 othing for granted about people's consent. </span><br><br><span>In the case
  of <strong>rain</strong>\, the dance will go on - if it's thundering\, we 
 will have to see (but come on out so we can figure it out together)!</span>
 </span></span><br><br><span><span><strong>No Zoom</strong> - Unfortunately\
 , the best venues we've found for in-person\, outdoor\, covered\, spacious 
 events do not work well for using internet.</span></span><br><br><span><spa
 n>Previously\, <strong>bathrooms </strong>were available at the nearby base
 ball field. We are not sure if they will be available every week.</span></s
 pan><br><br><span><span><br><span><strong>TONS OF FUN AND HAPPINESS • MUST 
 BE VACCINATED AND BECOME A MEMBER </strong></span></span></span>
