CREATED:20220330T010526Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Registration is now closed - see you there if
  you've registered! (Otherwise\, we hope to catch you next year) <br><br>Ra
 nsburg Boy Scout Camp<br><br>(located near Bloomington on beautiful Monroe 
 Lake)<br><br><br><span><span><span><b>Protocol Reminders</b></span></span><
 /span><br><span><span>• All attendees must&nbsp\;<b>pre-register </b>by Aug
 ust 18 for the whole weekend - there will be no walk-ins this year\, and no
  a la carte registration (also no musicians jamming outside without registe
 ring - sorry about that!). (Also no splitting of registration between peopl
 e.) You can arrive late or leave early\, but you still need to register for
  the whole weekend. Please also be mindful of not timing your arrival for t
 he middle of the night or very early in the morning\, as our registration v
 olunteers need to be on hand when you arrive.</span></span><u></u><u></u><b
 r><u></u><u></u><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span>•&nbsp\;<b>Masks will be require
 d at all times while in the main dance building</b>&nbsp\;(including the ki
 tchen and side wings).&nbsp\;<b>No cloth masks</b>. You will need surgical 
 masks\, N95 masks\, or KN95 masks (N95 or KN95 much preferred). Masks must 
 be worn fully covering your nose and mouth. Meals will be outside and there
  will be no eating inside.&nbsp\;It is OK to pull your mask down to take wa
 ter breaks at the edge of the room during the dance. Thank you for helping 
 us make this work. In case of rain\, the protocol will change.</span></span
 ><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span>•&nbsp\;<b>Everyone will be required to complet
 e a rapid Covid test&nbsp\;<u>on arrival at <span>Sugar</span> <span>Hill</
 span></u></b>&nbsp\;and show a negative result\, as part of registration\, 
 before being allowed to complete your registration or take part in activiti
 es. This requirement will be repeated each day you are present (Friday and 
 Saturday\; no new test will be required on&nbsp\;Sunday morning).&nbsp\;<b>
 We will provide the Covid tests.&nbsp\;</b></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><sp
 an><span>(<i>Please note that we are not requiring that you show us an earl
 ier PCR or other kind of test\, but for your own sake\, so that you will no
 t have to come all the way to <span>Sugar</span> <span>Hill</span> and then
  turn around and go home\, we encourage you to take a rapid home test right
  before coming to the camp as well. In addition\, please have a plan in min
 d if you are arriving with others so that if one or more in your arrival gr
 oup test positive\, there is a transportation plan in place to get them hom
 e again.</i>)</span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span>•&nbsp\;<b>Refunds</b
 >: if you need to cancel because you are sick or have been exposed\, or if 
 you arrive at the camp and test positive and need to leave again\, we will 
 refund your entire registration fee (including cabin fees). Thank you so mu
 ch for helping to keep us all safe! If you would like to waive all or part 
 of your refund as a donation to us and to help us cover others' refunds\, w
 e will happily accept - just let us know.</span></span></html-blob><br><htm
 l-blob><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span><u></u></html-blob><br><html-blob><
 /html-blob><br><html-blob>• Reminder: <strong>all attendees must be up-to-d
 ate on COVID vaccinations</strong>. For our purposes\, this means that you 
 have had your initial Covid vaccine\, plus one booster shot\, if you qualif
 y for a booster. This means that if your 2nd dose of a Pfizer or Moderna va
 ccine was at least 6 months ago or your single dose of a Johnson &amp\; Joh
 nson vaccine was at least 2 months ago\, you will need to show us evidence 
 of a booster shot as well.<br><u></u><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span><u></
 u><br><u></u><span><span>More information about the weekend is available on
  our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/sugar-hill/"><b><u>website</u></
 b></a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/1548507412088405/"><b><
 u>Facebook page</u></b></a>. Reach out to <a href="mailto:sugarhill@bloomin
 gtoncontra.org"><span>sugarhill</span>@bloomingtoncontra.<u></u>org</a> wit
 h any questions.</span></span><u></u></html-blob>
