UID:6agtbnchmbdhffjp1qbrlsh6un@google.com
CREATED:20230123T212202Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>We're excited to announce that we will be offering a country
  waltzing workshop\, followed by an open waltzing hour\, on the following d
 ates:<br><b> </b></p><p><b>Sunday\, March 5th</b>\, at the Harmony School g
 ym (909 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN).<br><br><b>3 to 4 p.m.: Waltzing Works
 hop</b> led by Tamara Loewenthal (for beginning and intermediate waltzers)<
 br><br><b>4 to 5 p.m.: Open Waltzing</b>\, with Open Band hosted by Eric Sc
 hedler (for all levels of waltzers)\, all musicians welcome.</p><p>-------<
 br> </p><p>You are welcome to come for the workshop\, the open waltzing\, o
 r both\, as you would like. You can come on both dates or just one or the o
 ther. <br><br>Doors will open at 2:40\; please come early to sign in\, show
  your proof of vaccination (if non-member)\, take off your coat and change 
 your shoes\, and whatever else you need to do to be ready for the workshop 
 at 3:00!<br> </p><p>------<br> </p><p>*Special event\, membership not requi
 red</p><p>*Donation of $3 to $20 requested to help cover hall rental and in
 structor</p><p>*Vaccination protocols: non-members please bring proof of bi
 valent booster (or most recent booster if not yet eligible for bivalent)</p
 ><p>*Masks encouraged but not required<br><br>Come waltz with us\, and invi
 te your friends!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230131T192557Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Waltzing Workshop and Open Waltzing
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
