CREATED:20220702T175218Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Join us for our weekly Wednesday night contra
  dance!<br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Informati
 on</b></span></span></span><ul><li><span><span>7:30-9 p.m.<br></span></span
 ></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><span>Beginner lesson at 7:10 p.m. (try to 
 arrive by 7 to register as a member)<br></span></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;
  &nbsp\;&nbsp\; <br><li><span><span>Vaccines\, membership\, and masks requi
 red (see more details below)</span></span></li> &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<li><span><s
 pan>Entrance fee by donation after becoming a member (suggested range is $3
 -20\; if everyone pays ~$10\, we'll break even)</span></span></li></ul><spa
 n><span><span><b>Weekly Wednesday Dance Details</b></span><br><b>Up-to-date
  vaccination is required</b>. This means that if your 2nd dose of a Pfizer 
 or Moderna <span>vaccine</span> was at least 5 months ago or your single do
 se of a Johnson &amp\; Johnson <span>vaccine</span> was at least 2 months a
 go\, you will need to show us evidence of a booster shot. (For our purposes
 \, even if you are eligible for more than one booster shot\, only one is re
 quired.) If we have not yet seen proof of your most recent vaccination\, pl
 ease send a photo to <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">
 <b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></a> by the end of
  Tuesday\, or bring the card or a photo of it with you to the dance.<b><i> 
 </i></b>Thank you for helping to keep us all safe!</span><br><br><span><b>M
 embership is required.</b> Becoming a member is easy! 1) Fill <span>in a me
 mbership form at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-cont
 ent/uploads/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf"><b><u>print one</u></b></a> 
 to complete in advance. 2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><
 a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@<
 u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org </u></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance. 3) 
 Pay $12 either at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become
 -a-member/"><b><u>online</u></b></a> ($2 for those under 30). </span><br><b
 r><b>Masks are required. </b>Masks must cover the mouth and nose at all tim
 es in the dance hall and when entering the building. Dancers can step outsi
 de the dance hall to drink water. <br><br><b>This dance is run by donation<
 /b>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will giv
 e at least something because the event is sustained by the community. We es
 timate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would break even after paying
  the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be made <a href="http://b
 loomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">
 <b><u>online</u></b></a> or at the door.</span></span>&nbsp\;<u></u></html-
 blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231025T005312Z
LOCATION:Harmony School\, 909 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47401\, USA
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Contra Dance at Harmony School - Joanna Hyde (fiddle)\, Tadhg Ó Mea
 chair (accordion) and Eric Schedler (piano)\, with Mercury McGill calling 
