STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Zoom Event:  Cherylyn Geers (the Unamused Kraken) with Nicholas Roc
 kstroh
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20230309T003000Z
DTEND:20230309T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020722Z
UID:2tdnmhaipglpvj0nopl9dt3k3t@google.com
CREATED:20230302T142350Z
DESCRIPTION:<strong>About Our Dances</strong><ul><li><strong>Time: </strong
 >7:30-9:30 p.m.</li>   <li><strong>Location</strong>: Harmony School\, 909 
 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47401</li>   <li><strong>Entrance fee</strong>:
  by sliding scale donation\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope
  that everyone will give at least something because the event is sustained 
 by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to give $10\, we would 
 break even after paying the rental fee and the performers. Donations may be
  made <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u
 =0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=298b3f55c0&e=6f029e4d69"><u><b><u>online</u><
 /b></u></a> or at the door. </li>   <li><strong>Striving Toward Safe Space 
 Policy</strong>: We hope to create a dance in which everyone feels safe and
  welcome. Please take a moment to review our <a href="https://bloomingtonco
 ntra.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=5d4959
 b742&e=6f029e4d69"><u><b><u>policy</u></b></u></a> on respect and consent.<
 /li></ul><strong>Covid Policies</strong>   <br><ul><li><strong>Membership R
 equirement</strong>: Becoming a member is easy! Membership is optional the 
 first two times someone attends the dance in 2023.<br>   1) Fill out a memb
 ership form at the dance.<br>   2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to 
 <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><u><b><u>communicatio
 ns@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org </u></b></u></a>or bring it to the dance.<b
 r>   3) Pay $10 either at the dance or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.u
 s13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&id=92fa0d4267&e
 =6f029e4d69"><u><b><u>online</u></b></u></a> (free for those 15 and under).
  </li>   <li><strong>Up-to-Date Vaccination Requirement</strong>: All atten
 dees (dancers\, musicians\, callers\, observers) are required to have the m
 ost up-to-date COVID vaccine they are eligible for. Attendees may bring the
 ir most recent vaccine card to the dance or email a copy of it to <a href="
 mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org"><u>communications@<u></u>bloom
 ingtoncontra.org</u></a> by Tuesday night before the dance. (For most vacci
 nated people\, this means a bivalent booster after September 2 or having ha
 d COVID within the past 90 days.)</li>   <li><strong>Masks Encouraged</stro
 ng>: Additionally\, masks are required if you have been exposed to COVID re
 cently.</li>   <li><strong>Stay home if you...</strong>    <ul>       <li>h
 ave symptoms of COVID (which could also mean cold or flu symptoms)\, regard
 less of whether or not you tested for COVID</li>       <li>first tested pos
 itive for COVID within the last 5 days\, even without symptoms </li>       
 <li>first tested positive for COVID more than 5 days ago and still have a f
 ever\, and/or your symptoms are not yet getting better</li>  <br></ul></li>
 <li><strong>Exercise caution and wear a mask if... </strong>    <ul>       
 <li>you have been exposed to someone who has tested positive (spent more th
 an 15 minutes less than 6 feet away from them\, without masks on\, indoors\
 , or spent 20 minutes or more in intense conversation or close proximity ev
 en outdoors\, without masks on)        <ul>           <li>err on the conser
 vative side</li>           <li>watch yourself for symptoms</li>           <
 li>take a COVID test on day 5 </li></ul></li>       <li>If the exposure hap
 pened within 5 days of the dance\, it is probably wisest to stay home then\
 , too\, until you have a chance to test yourself. Please note that this is 
 more conservative than the CDC's guidelines at this point.</li></ul></li>  
  <li><strong>Notify us if...</strong><strong> </strong>   <ul>       <li>yo
 u are diagnosed with COVID-19 within 10 days of attending any BOTMDG event\
 , please let the board know\, at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomington
 contra.org"><u><b><u>communications@<u></u>bloomingtoncontra.org</u></b></u
 ></a>\, within 24 hours of your diagnosis if you possibly can\, so that we 
 can inform others.</li></ul></li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230302T142350Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Bob and Tom Show - Tom Cunningham (Fiddle) and Bob Douglas (Per
 cussion)\, with Katie Zukof calling
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
