UID:3r6466l02taiutl6fbt2kkuf27@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20211020T193000
CREATED:20210904T135422Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span>Join us in Ellettsville this Wednesday\, August 25\
 , 7:30-8:45 p.m.\, for live music\, calling and dancing! Rain or shine *or 
 heat advisory*\, but do bring your water bottle and plan to rest as needed.
  Remember\, our dance is outside\, under a roof at an outdoor shelter. Ther
 e was a lovely breeze last week so we will hope for something like that aga
 in\, and we'll have fans going\, too.<br><br><em>Remember\,&nbsp\;</em></sp
 an></span><em><span><span>masks are required at the check-in table for the 
 comfort and safety of check-in volunteers. Masks are encouraged at the danc
 e. Like last week\, we'll have</span></span></em><span><span><em> two <span
 >contra</span> lines - one with masks required and one with masks optional.
 </em></span></span> <em>Please also understand that we are monitoring the e
 volving Covid situation and our restrictions or arrangements may change on 
 short notice. </em><br><br><span><span><span><strong>Wednesday Night Dance 
 General Information</strong></span><br><span><strong>Vaccines are required<
 /strong>.&nbsp\;We will need to see your vaccination card\, if you haven't 
 already shared it with us. Either send a photo to <a href="mailto:communica
 tions@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@<wbr>bloomingtoncontra.org</a> 
 by the end of Tuesday\, or bring it with you to the dance. </span><br><br>T
 his is a <strong>members-only</strong> dance. Becoming a member is easy - <
 span>you can do so online at&nbsp\;<a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13.
 list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=fa7530d294&
 amp\;e=9fd49b8c10">http://bloomingtoncontra.<wbr>org/become-a-member/</a>\,
  or you can bring $12 to the dance. Note: membership for anyone under 30 ye
 ars old is only $2!</span><br><br><span>Dances begin at <strong>7:30 p.m. E
 astern</strong>. </span>The last waltz will conclude around 8:45 p.m. to al
 low time for cleanup. You are welcome to come early to help set up or stay 
 late to help pack up.<br><br>Events will be in-person at the Big Shelter at
  <strong>Marci Jane Lewis Park</strong>\, 106 South Park Street\, in Ellett
 sville - just 15 minutes from downtown Bloomington!<strong> </strong></span
 ></span><br><br><span><span><span>This dance is run <strong>by donation</st
 rong>\, with a suggested range from $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will g
 ive at least something because the event is sustained by the community. We 
 will continue to give 100% of the donations to the performers.</span> <span
 >Donations may be made in person or <a href="https://bloomingtoncontra.us13
 .list-manage.com/track/click?u=0c065082be7e5f22020734e68&amp\;id=3e372e0a45
 &amp\;e=9fd49b8c10">here</a>.</span></span></span><br><br><span><span><span
 ><strong>Participate at your comfort level. </strong>There is plenty of spa
 ce to spread out and listen to the music\, watch the dances\, or dance alon
 e\, as a couple\, in a small pod\, or in a <span>contra</span> line. Please
  do not assume what others are comfortable with - ask! We will </span></spa
 n></span> <span>be distributing colored wristbands to indicate comfort with
  different levels of interaction.</span><br><br><span><span><span>In the ca
 se of <strong>rain</strong>\, the dance will go on - if it's thundering\, w
 e will have to see (but come on out so we can figure it out together)!</spa
 n></span></span><br><br><span><span><strong>No Zoom</strong> - Unfortunatel
 y\, the best venues we've found for in-person\, outdoor\, covered\, spaciou
 s events do not work well for using internet.</span></span><br><br><span><s
 pan>Previously\, <strong>bathrooms </strong>were available at the nearby ba
 seball field. We are not sure if they will be available every week.</span><
 /span>
