DTSTAMP:20260309T020722Z
UID:73e0td7cmkvojv8i10lshgd3k0@google.com
CREATED:20210226T221222Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>With Mo Brachfeld on fiddle and Jared Kirkpatrick on pian
 o\, mandolin\, and feet\, Starling creates a contemporary contra dance soun
 d from bringing together the roots of Irish\, Scottish\, New England\, Queb
 ecois\, and Appalachian fiddle music. The two have played together for a ye
 ar and a half\, and are excited to enter the world of Zoom dances!  Meg Ded
 olph is a Chicago-area dance caller with a deeply weird repertoire\, which 
 allows her to call contra dances for rooms full of enthusiasts and newcomer
 s\, to teach Irish set dances at Morris dance weekends or to call a night o
 f unplanned triplets during a snowstorm. She is a regular caller at her hom
 e dance series as well as at church harvest festivals and weddings\, and sh
 e and her partner plan to resume running their all-ages barn dance series a
 s soon as current events permit. Her walkthroughs are fast and concise\, sh
 e is sometimes funny\, and she just wants everyone to have a good time.</sp
 an><br><span>&nbsp\;&nbsp\; <span><br><span>---------- </span><br>&nbsp\;<b
 r><span><span><span>If you'd like the Zoom link\, please email us at <span>
 <span>at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communicatio
 ns@bloomingtoncontra.org</a></span></span>.</span></span></span><br><span><
 span><span>As of March\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dances begin at <b>8 p.m. Eas
 tern</b>.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you haven
 ’t been to one of our online events\, you might be wondering what to expect
 ! As our musicians play for us\, and the caller calls\, you are welcome to 
 dance with us in your own space\, play along with the musicians with your m
 ic muted\, or just watch and listen. We also try to check in with everyone 
 briefly each week. The music lasts until about 8:45\, followed by the check
 -in.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>Waltzes are easy 
 to dance alone or with a partner. Up-tempo tunes will sometimes have <span>
 contra</span>-like calling\, but for the times when there is no calling\, p
 lease feel free to dance along at home with <span>contra</span> moves of yo
 ur choice. Or just boogie down to the amazing music!</span></span>&nbsp\; <
 /span><br><br><span>----------</span><span><br></span><br><span>We are grat
 eful for all donations\, and happy to be able to keep paying our musicians 
 and dance leaders during these unusual times. You can find our <a href="htt
 p://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-during-the-covid-19-downti
 me/">PayPal donation button on our website</a>.&nbsp\; </span></span> </spa
 n>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210226T222435Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Zoom Event: Starling (Mo Brachfeld and Jared Kirkpatrick) with Meg 
 Dedolph calling
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
