DESCRIPTION:<span>You can find&nbsp\;</span><a href="http://bloomingtoncont
 ra.org/botmdg-general-membership-meeting-agenda/">the&nbsp\; meeting agenda
 </a><span>&nbsp\;and&nbsp\;</span><a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/sla
 tes-of-candidates-for-board-positions-2021/">the slates for the election of
  the 2021 board</a><span>&nbsp\;on our website.&nbsp\;</span><br><br><span>
 To take part and be able to vote on next year's board members as well as th
 e proposed amendments to the bylaws\, you need to be a member. Annual membe
 rship is $12\, or $2 if you are under 30. Considering the unusual situation
 \, the Board voted earlier this year to continue all 2020 memberships throu
 gh the end of 2021. To become a member\, go to&nbsp\;</span><a href="http:/
 /bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/">http://bloomingtoncontra.org/<wbr>
 become-a-member/</a><span>.</span><br><br><span>If you donated more than $1
 2 this year\, you are eligible to designate the first $12 as your membershi
 p fee. We recently contacted all of this year's donors who were not already
  members\, but if you have donated since then and would like to become a me
 mber using the first $12 as your fee\, please let us know at&nbsp\;</span><
 a href="mailto:communications@bloomingtoncontra.org">communications@<wbr>bl
 oomingtoncontra.org</a><span>&nbsp\;before January 18th. Likewise\, if you 
 are unsure about your membership status\, please contact us at that e-mail 
 address before that date.</span><br><font><span><span></span></span></font>
