CREATED:20231205T002408Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join Sam Bartlett for a weekly one hour session of fun\, soc
 ial tune learning\, dance musician tips\, and rhythm strengthening exercise
 s to make your dance musicianship soar!</p><p>The class is aimed toward mus
 icians over 55\, but open to anyone.</p><p>It will be held at 6 p.m. on Wed
 nesdays before the dance:</p><p>Nov. 29: Harmony gym (909 E 2nd St)<br>Dec.
  6\, 13: Harmony gym<br>Dec. 20: Serendipity (201 S College Ave)<br>Jan. 3\
 , 10\, 17: Harmony gym</p><p>Culminating with the dance band class playing 
 the dance January 24th.</p><p>Every class will feature 1 to 2 new tunes tau
 ght slowly by ear\, along with the chords and other accompaniment ideas. In
  addition\, participants will practice next to each other\, finding the rhy
 thmic sweet spot of contra dance\, 110 BPM.</p><p>Local dancers and musicia
 ns know Sam\, but might not know:</p><p>He has played in virtually every ol
 d-time and contra dance community in the United States for the past 40 year
 s\, and has played with a who’s who of touring dance bands including: Wild 
 Asparagus\, the Clayfoot Strutters\, Notorious\, Rodney Miller and the Stri
 ngrays\, the Monks\, and of course Bloomington’s own Supertrad\, with Eric 
 Schedler.<br><br>For questions\, contact Sam at: sam@sambartlett.com. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231205T002408Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tune class with Sam Bartlett
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
