UID:4ju014t9g6rhqsk260qqnqqc1t@google.com
CREATED:20210328T145714Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Sam Bartlett and Eric Schedler of Bloomington\, Indiana a
 re a tour de force of traditional dance music and the finest accordion/banj
 o duo in the Midwest. Though they are steeped in the subtle intricacies of 
 the old Celtic and New England tune traditions\, they play with an emotion\
 , groove and persistence that is timeless.&nbsp\;</span><br><span>&nbsp\;</
 span><br><span>Brian Lindsay joins them from Washington state on fiddle and
  feet.  Brian is a contest-winning Irish-style fiddle player\, singer\, com
 poser\, and half of the Countercurrent duo.&nbsp\;</span><br><span>&nbsp\;<
 /span><br><span>Meg Dedolph is a Chicago-area dance caller with a deeply we
 ird repertoire\, which allows her to call contra dances for rooms full of e
 nthusiasts and newcomers\, to teach Irish set dances at Morris dance weeken
 ds or to call a night of unplanned triplets during a snowstorm. She is a re
 gular caller at her home dance series as well as at church harvest festival
 s and weddings\, and she and her partner plan to resume running their all-a
 ges barn dance series as soon as current events permit. Her walkthroughs ar
 e fast and concise\, she is sometimes funny\, and she just wants everyone t
 o have a good time.</span><br><br>&nbsp\; <span><span><span><br><span>-----
 ----- </span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><span><span>If you'd like the Zoom link\,
  please email us at <span><span>at <a href="mailto:communications@bloomingt
 oncontra.org">communications@bloomingtoncontra.org</a></span></span>.</span
 ></span></span><br><span><span><span>As of March\, all BOTMDG Wednesday dan
 ces begin at <b>8 p.m. Eastern</b>.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><spa
 n><span><span>If you haven’t been to one of our online events\, you might b
 e wondering what to expect! As our musicians play for us\, and the caller c
 alls\, you are welcome to dance with us in your own space\, play along with
  the musicians with your mic muted\, or just watch and listen. We also try 
 to check in with everyone briefly each week. The music lasts until about 8:
 45\, followed by the check-in.</span></span></span><br>&nbsp\;<br><span><sp
 an><span>Waltzes are easy to dance alone or with a partner. Up-tempo tunes 
 will sometimes have <span>contra</span>-like calling\, but for the times wh
 en there is no calling\, please feel free to dance along at home with <span
 >contra</span> moves of your choice. Or just boogie down to the amazing mus
 ic!</span></span>&nbsp\; </span><br><br><span>----------</span><span><br></
 span><br><span>We are grateful for all donations\, and happy to be able to 
 keep paying our musicians and dance leaders during these unusual times. You
  can find our <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-performers-
 during-the-covid-19-downtime/">PayPal donation button on our website</a>.&n
 bsp\;&nbsp\; </span></span></span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210328T145714Z
