 eep us all safe!</span></span><span><span><br><br><strong>Membership is req
 uired.</strong> Becoming a members is easy! 1) fill <span>in a membership f
 orm at the dance or <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/wp-content/upload
 s/2022/01/BOTMDG_memberform2022.pdf">print one</a> to complete in advance. 
 2) Send proof of up-to-date vaccination to </span><a href="mailto:communica
 tions@bloomingtoncontra.org"><b><u>communications@bloomingtoncontra.org </u
 ></b></a><span>or bring it to the dance. 3) Pay $12 either at the dance or 
 <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/become-a-member/">online</a> ($2 for 
 those under 30). </span><br><br><strong>Masks are required. </strong>Masks 
 must cover the mouth and nose at all times. Dancers can step outside for a 
 mask break or may step into the hallway to take a drink of water.<br><br><s
 trong>This dance is run by donation</strong>\, with a suggested range from 
 $3 to $20. We hope that everyone will give at least something because the e
 vent is sustained by the community. We estimate that if everyone were to gi
 ve $10\, we would break even after paying the rental fee and the performers
 . Donations may be made <a href="http://bloomingtoncontra.org/support-our-p
 erformers-during-the-covid-19-downtime/">online</a> or at the door.</span><
 /span><br><br><span>&nbsp\;</span>&nbsp\;<span><span></span></span></html-b
 lob>
